(49, 'Divorce and Separation', 'divorce_and_seperation', 'Specialist Divorce Solicitors', 49, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Need to get out of your relationship?</h2>\r\n<p>You are probably worrying about where you are going to live, whether you''ll keep your children and how much money you will have. Don''t worry we are here to help you with all the legal issues that arise when relationships break up. Whether you are married, or have been living with your partner, our experienced team will advise you on resolving these&nbsp;issues and help you get the best outcome to suit your needs.</p>\r\n<p>Many of our clients also worry about going to Court when they come to see us, but be assured that there are several options available that will avoid you going to Court. Collaborative law is one of the modern approaches to family breakdown and has been labelled as a &ldquo;good&rdquo; divorce as you agree from the outset that you will not go to Court.&nbsp; We do appreciate however, that not all cases are the same and if going to Court is your chosen route then we''ll be with you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<h2>Why choose Banner Jones Solicitors?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We have one of the largest Family Law teams in NE Derbyshire and Sheffield</li>\r\n<li>You have a choice of&nbsp;5 offices across Chesterfield, Bolsover, Clay Cross, Dronfield and Sheffield</li>\r\n<li>We have a mixed team of male and female divorce lawyers so if you have a preference then you can choose who you see</li>\r\n<li>We are experienced in high value matrimonial cases</li>\r\n<li>We are Resolution accredited</li>\r\n<li>We have Collaborative lawyers in our team</li>\r\n<li>We have Children law specialists in our team</li>\r\n<li>We have an independent mediation service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If your financial&nbsp;circumstances&nbsp;are complex and you need advice on the division of high value matrimonial assets and property, &nbsp;then we have the experience to help you reach the best solution.</p>\r\n<p>Some couples are able to resolve their situation amicably through <a href="../../../page/mediation">Mediation</a>. Could this be right for you?</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/cohabitation-separation-and-divorce/?s=BAN082" target="_blank"></a></p>', '2010-11-15 10:34:24', '2014-02-12 14:15:28', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p><strong>Affordable&nbsp;Fixed Fee Divorce</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Giving you the choice...</strong></p>', '83_iStock_000007854419XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 99712, '2013-02-19 10:01:02', 'Divorce solicitor chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'DivorceAndSeparation.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 56028, '2011-01-13 16:16:24', 'Divorce and Separation', '', '', 'Divorce and Separation', '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', NULL, NULL),
(50, 'Children', 'children', 'What about the kids?', 50, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>You know your children better than anyone else and as a parent you are best placed to make the important decisions for them, but there may be times you need more help, support and guidance.</p>\r\n<p>If you have children and you are getting divorced, separating, or your cohabitation is breaking up, we can advise you on a wide range of issues relating to the children.</p>\r\n<p>As far as possible, we help you reach an amicable agreement which is always based upon what is in the children&rsquo;s &nbsp;best interests. However, where necessary, we can apply to the Courts for appropriate Orders.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For some examples of common issues and problems and how we can assist you click on the link.</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/parental-responsibility" target="_blank">Parental Responsibility </a>-what rights and responsibilities do both parents have</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/residence-orders" target="_blank">Residence Orders</a> - where should the children live and who should be the children&rsquo;s primary carer</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/contact-orders" target="_blank">Contact Orders</a> - what time should the children spend with each adult</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/mediation" target="_blank">Mediation</a> -non-court based process with trained neutral mediators</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/collaborative-law" target="_blank">Collaborative law</a> -non-court based lawyer supported negotiation</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/applying-to-court" target="_blank">Applying to Court</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/care-proceedings" target="_blank">Care Proceedings</a>- where there is social services intervention in the Children&rsquo;s care</p>\r\n<p>Helena Downing, Kevin Tomlinson and Diane Gunn are all on the Law Society''s Children&rsquo;s panel. Only solicitors who meet the Law Society&rsquo;s exacting accreditation requirements are permitted to join the Children Panel and represent children in public law care proceedings.&nbsp; Your skills, knowledge and experience are rigorously and independently assessed in order to achieve this accreditation status. This means that you know you are dealing with the very best .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/50/contained_images/f16c92303bc3_136_children law.jpg?1320769561" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">For a Fixed Fee Interview, which includes a free half hour please contact us today</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>', '2010-11-15 10:34:39', '2014-02-12 14:20:29', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p><strong>First 30 Minutes FREE</strong></p>', '158_woman and child.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 274596, '2012-02-24 14:26:05', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Children.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 53936, '2011-01-13 14:48:27', 'Children', '', '', 'Children', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(51, 'Cohabitation', 'cohabitation', 'Does not being married worry you?', 51, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Break-up of a relationship</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The law treats unmarried couples differently from married couples. Our knowledge of this complex area of law can help you resolve your problems following break-up with a cohabitation partner.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Much can be done to protect your interests, including your financial assets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If there are children from the relationship, we can help you to agree arrangements for them.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Cohabitation agreements</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Did you know that...</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">There is no such thing as a &ldquo;common law&rdquo; husband and wife? </li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">If a co-habitee dies the survivor is not his or her &ldquo;next of kin&rdquo; and therefore may have to go to court to claim all or any of the deceased&rsquo;s estate? </li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">You may not automatically be responsible for any surviving children of the relationship? </li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">A co-habitee does not automatically acquire an interest in his or her partner&rsquo;s property simply by living there for a certain period of time; and that the law in this area is so complex that some Judges struggle to make sense of it? </li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Even if you own property together, you may not own it equally (especially if it was bought before 1996) and that a recent case has stated that, in certain situations, the value of that house may not automatically be shared equally between former co-habitees? </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A Cohabitation agreement can help remove some of the above uncertainties. If you are going to live with a partner but not marry, it is sensible to create an agreement which records your intentions about your assets and how you would share or divide them if your relationship broke up. We can draft an agreement which states your intentions and protects your financial assets.</p>', '2010-11-15 10:34:57', '2014-02-12 14:20:53', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Protect your assets with a Will</p>', '43_hand and keys.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 53480, '2011-04-14 15:26:06', NULL, 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Cohabitation.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 52209, '2011-01-13 14:48:45', 'Cohabitation', '', '', 'Cohabitation', '/page/making-a-will', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(52, 'Domestic Violence', 'domestic_violence', 'You are not on your own', 52, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">We have one of the largest family law teams in the area which enables us to respond very quickly if you are suffering violence from anyone with whom you have a domestic relationship, or have been in the past. It may be your spouse, partner, or even your child. The violence may be physical or psychological.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our approach will be to consider how best to protect you. This may involve making an application for an injunction from the court in order to stop the person coming near you. It may carry a Power of Arrest to give you effective protection.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you need a solicitor to act for you quickly, telephone us on 01246 560 560.</p>', '2010-11-15 10:35:14', '2014-02-12 14:20:55', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Here for you</p>', '181_New family march 13.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 227542, '2013-03-28 10:57:27', NULL, 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'DomesticViolence.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 53960, '2011-01-13 14:49:03', 'Domestic Violence', '', '', 'Domestic Violence', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(53, 'Pre or Postmarital/Partnership Agreements', 'pre_marital_agreements', 'Pre and Post Nuptial Agreements', 53, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Do I need one?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">With high profile cases such as the Mills and McArtney raising the profile of acrimonious settlements, it is little surprise that couples thinking of marrying would now give consideration to some sort of pre marital prenuptial agreements.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Who should consider a pre or post-marital/partnership agreement?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Agreements of this nature are particularly worth considering if:-</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>One or both of the parties to the relationship are more mature. </li>\r\n<li>Where this may be his second marriage or partnership. </li>\r\n<li>Where one party brings significant assets to a relationship or there is an imbalance in the financial provision to be made by both parties. </li>\r\n<li>Where provision needs to be made for children or dependants from a previous relationship. </li>\r\n<li>Where you wish to influence how assets may be divided between you should the marriage or civil partnership fail.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">When should we consider these types of agreements?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As soon as possible. The longer the agreement is in place prior to a marriage or civil partnership being entered into the better. However, agreements entered into after marriage or Civil Partnership can still have legal effect.&nbsp; In order for an agreement of this nature to be made binding there needs to be independent legal advice for both parties, full and frank financial disclosure and no duress.&nbsp; If a pre-nuptial agreement of this nature is entered into at the church door then it is open to an allegation that one party or the other has been under a level of duress to enter into the agreement.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Are pre or postnuptial agreements binding?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Prenuptial agreements are common place on mainland Europe but the courts in England and Wales have always been reluctant to have their overall discretion as to how assets should be divided upon divorce tied in by an agreement reached between two parties prior to the marriage taking place.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A gradual shift towards recognising the validity of pre and post nuptial agreements was brought to a head by the case of <strong>Radmacher v. Grantino</strong>. This case went to the highest court in the land, The Supreme Court, purely on whether a pre-nuptial agreement entered into by the parties in Germany three months before they married was applicable in law in England and Wales.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Supreme Court decided in October 2010 that it was natural to infer that parties entering into agreements of this sort will intend that legal effect would be given to those agreements. Unless the outcome of the pre-nuptial agreement was unfair to any children of the marriage, in which case the court could still ignore or vary the agreement, the agreement would be upheld by the court.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">How do I found out more?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Please contact any member of the family team who would be able to discuss the options available with you.</p>', '2010-11-15 10:35:37', '2014-02-12 14:20:59', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Contacts us today to get your agreement in place</p>', '58_iStock_000000753188XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 144736, '2011-03-04 16:11:24', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'PartnershipAgreements.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 42618, '2011-01-13 14:49:43', 'Pre or Postmarital/Partnership Agreements', '', '', 'Pre or Postmarital/Partnership Agreements', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(54, 'Civil Partnerships', 'civil_partnerships', 'Civil Partnerships', 54, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;">What are Civil Partnerships?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Civil partnerships are for adult same sex couples who are not in existing registered partnerships or marriage and are not closely related.&nbsp; Couples who register have legal status as &ldquo;registered civil partners&rdquo; and acquire a package of rights and responsibilities in the same way as a married couple.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">What happens if my Civil Partnership does not work?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If the civil partnership breaks down then you can apply to the court to have the partnership brought to an end after you have been together as civil partners for at least one year.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is known as a Dissolution.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">How do I end my Civil Partnership?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Bringing the relationship to an end involves the similar process to having a divorce.&nbsp; A petition is filed asking that the partnership should be brought to a conclusion and showing that the partnership has definitely come to an end.&nbsp; The petition will need to be lodged with a County Court that specifically deals with dissolving civil partnerships.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">What basis can the partnership be ended by the Court?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The court will accept similar grounds to prove that the relationship has come to an end as those of divorcing couples.&nbsp; The ground for dissolution is that the relationship has broken down irretrievably shown by the following facts:-</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Either that your civil partner&rsquo;s behaviour has been so unreasonable you can no longer bear to live with him or her;</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">That you or your civil partner have lived apart for at least two years immediately preceding the presentation of the petition and your partner agrees to a dissolution;</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">That you and your civil partner have lived apart for at least five years prior to the presentation of the petition and the partner&rsquo;s consent is not required, or;</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Your civil partner has deserted you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For a desertion petition you will need to have been apart for two years immediately preceding the presentation of the petition.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Can I make financial claims against my civil partner if the partnership is brought to a conclusion?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Civil partners can make claims against each other&rsquo;s finances in the same way that heterosexual married couples can.&nbsp; If there are financial issues stemming from your separation and dissolution of the partnership you will need to take further detailed advice and we recommend that you contact one of the family team who can give you specific advice in relation to this complex area of law.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">What if there are children involved?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Following a dissolution we can apply to the Courts&nbsp; for orders&nbsp;regarding&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; children issues including residence, contact order and financial provision.&nbsp; See our <a href="../../../page/children" target="_blank">Children</a> page for more details.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Are there any useful sites for me to look at?</h2>\r\n<p>We recommended you look at the following websites:-</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.stonewall.org.uk/">www.stonewall.org.uk</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.hmcourts-service.gov.uk">www.hmcourts-service.gov.uk</a> to look at the paperwork involved in dissolving the civil partnership</p>', '2010-11-15 10:35:57', '2014-02-12 14:20:59', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Protect your assets with a Will</p>\r\n<p>Don''t leave it too late</p>', '102_iStock_000012393462XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 57204, '2011-04-14 15:30:19', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'CivilPartnerships.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 51597, '2011-01-13 14:51:20', 'Civil Partnerships', '', '', 'Civil Partnerships', '/page/making-a-will', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/making-a-will', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(61, 'Criminal Defence', 'crime', 'Criminal Defence', 61, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h1><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Please note: From 5pm on Friday 24th April 2015 the Banner Jones Solicitors Criminal Defence department became part of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vhsfletchers.co.uk" target="_blank">VHS Fletchers Solicitors</a>.<br /><br /></strong><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">As a result, if you have a live Criminal Defence matter this has been automatically been transferred.</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><span><br /></span></strong><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">We''re on your side...</span></p>\r\n<p>Our highly regarded Criminal Defence team in Chesterfield represent defendants in all types of cases including:</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>Theft and Fraud</li>\r\n<li>Burglary and Robbery</li>\r\n<li>Assault and Wounding</li>\r\n<li>Possession and Supply of drugs</li>\r\n<li>Firearms offences</li>\r\n<li>Rape, Manslaughter and Murder</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Several&nbsp;of our criminal&nbsp;solicitors in Chesterfield&nbsp;are accredited by the Law Society''s Criminal Litigation panel which means that&nbsp;they have gone through rigorous checks and can offer you the very best in advice.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Police Station</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; we have accredited Police Station Representatives in Chesterfield who will give expert legal advice to those in police custody on a 24-hour basis. If you need to contact a duty solicitor out of hours please call our criminal emergency number&nbsp;<strong><a href="tel: +441246283000">01246 283000</a></strong>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Magistrates Court</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; we support each client, make thorough preparations, and provide advocacy or instruct a barrister on your behalf.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Crown Court</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; we provide advice and support including the preparation of the case, gathering witness statements, and briefing your barrister.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Legal Aid</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Many of our clients are entitled to Legal Aid. If costs have to be paid on a private basis, we give an estimate of the likely costs at the outset.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment, <strong>call&nbsp;<strong><strong><a href="tel: +441246283000">01246 283000</a></strong></strong>&nbsp;or email <a href="mailto:chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk">chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk</a>.</strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/61/contained_images/e9c9dfd555a5_138_crim lit.JPG?1320854744" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></p>', '2010-11-15 10:52:51', '2015-08-12 13:08:14', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p><strong>Out of Hours help number:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong style="color: #ffffff; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 12px;"><a href="tel:+441246283000" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ffffff;">01246 283000</span></a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Call our Chesterfield duty solicitor on this number if you need support out of office hours</strong></p>', '88_iStock_000008392789XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 232600, '2011-03-04 16:43:48', 'criminal defence solicitor chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'CriminalDefence.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 28550, '2011-07-29 14:28:58', 'Criminal Defence', '', '', 'Criminal Defence', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', ''),
(62, 'Wills', 'wills', 'Making a Will | Will Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 62, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 class="Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1" style="text-align: left;">Thinking about the unthinkable</h2>\r\n<p class="Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1" style="text-align: left;">Making a Will is often seen as a daunting prospect for a lot of people but here at Banner Jones we&rsquo;ll take you through it step by step ensuring that your Will represents everything you want it to. Most of our clients say it&rsquo;s such a relief to have finally done it and usually they have been putting it off for ages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Making a Will is commonly associated as something you do in later life however, in reality anyone over the age of 18 can have a Will and we would strongly recommend it to anyone with children. Wills are not for just sorting out finances and property in the event of your death, you can appoint guardians for your children and even leave money to your friends or a charity. Without a Will the government decides these things for you.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Read our <a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/14_Factsheet - 10 Reasons why you need a Will.doc?1322580008" target="_blank">free guide</a>&nbsp;now which will give you 10 reasons why you should have a Will.</h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Why Use Banner Jones?</h2>\r\n<ul style="text-align: left;">\r\n<li>Highly regarded team of qualified Wills solicitors</li>\r\n<li>FREE secure Will storage for life</li>\r\n<li>Members of ''the Certainty'' national Will register</li>\r\n<li>Appointments not always necessary</li>\r\n<li>Quick turnaround</li>\r\n<li>Home visits available</li>\r\n<li>Witnesses provided</li>\r\n<li>We''ll give you tax advice as part of the process</li>\r\n<li>Fixed Fee Promise on all Wills</li>\r\n<li>We will cover every detail leaving you able to relax</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>For more information about Wills, or to arrange an appointment, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:53:07', '2015-07-22 11:11:19', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Solicitors are insured and regulated.</p>\r\n<p>Will writers are not.</p>\r\n<p>Protect your family properly</p>', '84_iStock_000007985661XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 174578, '2011-03-04 16:19:43', 'Wills solicitor chesterfield and sheffield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Wills.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 51009, '2011-01-12 13:00:19', 'Wills', '', '', 'Wills', '/page/making-a-will', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '<p>Register your Will today</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Our Wills now include FREE registration on the national Will register, Certainty</p>', '/page/making-a-will', '', 'CertaintyNewLogo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 44741, '2012-06-12 12:16:56', 'wills solicitor chesterfield and sheffield', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/61_Family - Wills 2011 - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883400" target="_blank">Download Banner Jones Wills Leaflet</a></p>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/260_Family - Wills 2011.png?1396885003" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></p>', '', ''),
(63, 'Making a Will', 'making_a_will', 'Making a Will | Probate Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 63, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: left;">Writing a Will could be the most important thing you''ll ever do.</h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Not sure where to start?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">To help get you started here are a few things to think about when preparing to write your Will.</p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">Your Estate</h3>\r\n<ul style="text-align: left;">\r\n<li style="text-align: left;">Make a list of everything you own and what it is worth (assets)</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: left;">Include any life insurance policies and pension assets (if not already assigned)</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: left;">Subtract any money you may owe on death, such as mortgages and loans (liabilities)</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: left;">Estimate how much your estate is likely to be (the difference between your assets and liabilities)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">The Beneficiaries</h3>\r\n<ul style="text-align: left;">\r\n<li>Make a list of those whom you want to benefit, including names and addresses. Think about any&nbsp;wider family and friends also</li>\r\n<li>Think about who you would like to be guardians for your children and seek their approval</li>\r\n<li>Think about whether you want to leave gifts to any charities. See our <a href="../../../page/legacies" target="_blank">legacies</a>&nbsp;page for more information</li>\r\n<li>Make a note of who you DON''T want to benefit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Once you have all of this information you are ready to start drafting your Will</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Reviewing your Will</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Circumstances change over time so we advise that our clients review their Will every 5 years to ensure it still meets their needs. For example you may have moved house, gone through a divorce or maybe even had more Children/Grandchildren in that time.&nbsp; Some people may change their Will several times over their lifetime and there is no limit to how many times you can do this.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with an expert, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:55:49', '2015-07-22 11:17:39', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Starting a Family?</p>\r\n<p>It''s time to write&nbsp;a Will</p>', '82_iStock_000007694576XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 124876, '2011-03-28 14:47:21', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'MakingAWill.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 50736, '2011-01-11 11:51:49', 'Making a Will', '', '', 'Making a Will', '', '', 9, 'family_highlight', 'All of our Wills now include FREE registration on to the national Will register, Certainty', '', '', '170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 44954, '2012-06-12 12:18:56', '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/61_Family - Wills 2011 - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883400" target="_blank">Download Banner Jones Wills Leaflet</a></p>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/260_Family - Wills 2011.png?1396885003" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></p>', '', ''),
(64, 'Buy Online', 'buy_online', 'Buy Online', 64, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>Making a Will is much easier than most people think and we&rsquo;ve made it even easier by giving you a choice of how you go about it.<strong>&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Buy      Online. Make a standard Will today. Fill out the forms online and we&rsquo;ll check over the document for you and make sure that it suits your      needs.</li>\r\n<li>By      Appointment. Visit us in one of our offices to go through your wishes in      detail with a solicitor.&nbsp; This      option is best if you need tax planning advice or are looking to set up      trusts in your Will.</li>\r\n</ol> We come to your home or care home and take your wishes from you, sending the Will out to you for signatures.', '2010-11-15 10:56:10', '2014-03-31 10:19:04', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'BuyOnline.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 35538, '2011-01-11 11:43:45', 'Buy Online', '', '', 'Buy Online', '', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', NULL),
(65, 'Legacies', 'legacies', 'Leaving A Gift in Your Will | Probate Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 65, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: left;">Leaving money to charity in your Will can be a very satisfying thing to do, perhaps because they&rsquo;ve helped you or your loved ones in the past and you want to thank them for their hard work by leaving them a gift.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">There are two ways you can decide to leave money.&nbsp; You can&nbsp; leave either a residuary gift which is a % share&nbsp;of your final estate (once your family have been provided for), or&nbsp;you can specify the amount of money you wish to leave (A pecuniary gift).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">All gifts to charity in your Will are exempt from Inheritance Tax.&nbsp; These gifts are taken out of your estate before any inheritance tax is worked out, so there may be times when a gift to charity could substantially reduce the tax on your estate.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We work in partnership with several different charities and you could help us to help them by leaving a gift in your Will.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<a href="http://www.wphcc.org.uk/legacy" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/65/contained_images/ffbae737d4fa_13_wphcc.gif?1295369771" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Leaving a gift in your will to the Cancer Charity will have huge benefits not only for patients being treated now, but also for those who will be treated in the future.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">It is a simple process to leave a legacy to Weston Park Hospital Cancer Charity, either by making a Will if you do not have one, or by amending your existing Will.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>To talk to us about this, or any other aspect of Wills,&nbsp;call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span>*&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:56:23', '2015-07-22 11:18:49', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'Did you know over 50% of some charities income comes from the legacies people leave in their Will?', '85_iStock_000008248810XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 73750, '2011-03-04 16:20:50', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Legacies.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 44462, '2011-01-11 11:51:03', 'Legacies', '', '', 'Legacies', '/page/making-a-will', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/making-a-will', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', ''),
(66, 'Probate', 'probate', 'Probate Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 66, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: left;">To be able to administer the wishes set out in a Will you will need to apply for probate (technically known as applying for a Grant of Probate or granting of probate).</p>\r\nApplying for Probate is an order of the Court giving one or more people the legal authority to administer the estate of the deceased in order to distribute it correctly to the beneficiaries (i.e. probate of will).<br />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you have any asset worth over &pound;5,000, any stocks and shares or a property then your executors will usually need to apply for probate. If you don&rsquo;t make a Will, they need to apply for Letters of Administration instead, which is very similar. A probate valuation will help you find out what your assets are worth.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Unless your assets are all owned jointly with someone else and will pass to them automatically, you will need a Probate solicitor before your estate can be paid out. We can provide detailed advice about this if you need it.</p>\r\n<p>With our Fixed Fee promise after discussing the case with you we will fix your fee for our probate assistance so you know exactly what you will pay from the start.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have thought about how to probate yourself then please be aware that you will be required to attend a personal interview at the Probate Registery in Sheffield.&nbsp; As solicitors we can prepare the oath for you (at a lower fee) as part of our probate services which then saves you an additional&nbsp;trip to the Registery.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to take advantage of our probate advisory service, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:56:37', '2015-07-22 11:20:41', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'If you need to sell a home as part of the probate we can help you with this', '62_iStock_000002026541XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 253141, '2011-03-23 12:26:49', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Probate.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 64373, '2011-01-11 11:52:24', 'Probate', '', '', 'Probate', '/page/selling', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/selling', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', ''),
(67, 'Inheritance Tax', 'inheritance_tax', 'Inheritance Tax -The Facts | Probate Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 67, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: left;">Currently Inheritance Tax is a tax payable on death at the rate of 40% on the value of your net assets over &pound;325,000. The first &pound;325,000 is called the Nil Rate Band because although it is taxable to Inheritance Tax, it is taxed at 0%.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you are married, the best way to pay less inheritance tax (or even none at all) is by making inheritance tax efficient Wills. We can help you do this.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Here are some Frequently Asked Questions:</p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">1. Can&rsquo;t I just give some assets away, so I leave less than the Nil Rate Band when I die?</h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you give away large amounts of money, or valuable assets whilst you are alive, you must survive this gift for 7 years otherwise the Inland Revenue will tax you as if you still owned them when you die. This is the case whether you make the gift to an individual or put it into some types of trust.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you put your money or assets into certain types of trust or give them to a company, however, there is an immediate charge to inheritance tax &ndash; even though you are still alive.</p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">2. So, I can&rsquo;t give anything away whilst I am alive unless I survive for 7 years?</h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">There are certain gifts you can make which are not subject to this 7 year rule. Everyone has an &ldquo;annual exemption&rdquo; for inheritance tax of &pound;3,000 each every tax year. That means you can give away &pound;3,000 in total every tax year and it immediately falls out of your estate for inheritance tax purposes. If you die within 7 years, that gift will not be brought back into account. If you haven&rsquo;t used your annual exemption one year, you can roll it forward for 1 tax year, so you can give away &pound;6,000 the next year. You can only do this once, however.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">All gifts to UK charity, registered housing associations, qualifying political parties, national museums and universities are also exempt form inheritance tax altogether, whether you give to them under your Will or during your lifetime.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If your children or grandchildren get married, you can give them or their new spouse a lump sum of &pound;5,000 or &pound;2,500 respectively, completely free of inheritance tax.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">You can give any amount to your own spouse free of inheritance tax (provided you are both domiciled in England and Wales) although you should seek legal advice before doing so, as this could affect other tax planning possibilities.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">There are other gifts which are exempt from inheritance tax &ndash; please telephone or call into one of our offices to arrange an appointment and we will be happy to discuss these further.</p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">3. If I do decide to give a large amount to my children now, is there anything I can do to reduce the tax?</h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">You can insure the inheritance tax liability which would arise if you were to die within 7 years of the gift. Please ask for more information and one of our specialist advisers will be delighted to explain how this works and, if you wish, put you in touch with a trusted financial expert to help you choose the right policy for you.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>For more information Inheritance Tax, or to arrange an appointment with an expert, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:57:46', '2015-07-22 11:19:12', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>For more FREE information on Trusts and Inheritance Tax please click here</p>', '78_iStock_000006000433XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 189291, '2011-03-04 16:21:53', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'InheritanceTax.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 35556, '2011-01-11 11:47:27', 'Inheritance Tax', '', '', 'Inheritance Tax', '', 'http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/family-trusts-and-inheritance-tax/?s=BAN082', 9, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/61_Family - Wills 2011 - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883400" target="_blank">Download Banner Jones Wills Leaflet</a></p>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/260_Family - Wills 2011.png?1396885003" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ''),
(68, 'Trusts', 'trusts', 'A good way to protect your assets', 68, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Trusts can be used as a way of protecting your assets.&nbsp;&nbsp;They allow for property and assets to be held by trustees for the benefit of one or more individuals - these can be adult or children.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These individuals are known as the beneficiaries.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Commonly trusts are set up for assets to be held for the benefit of children until they reach a certain age.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Trusts are&nbsp;taxed independently for income tax, capital gains tax and inheritance tax purposes. This makes them an effective means of separating your estate to avoid tax.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A trust means that you assign responsibility of the finances over to a trustee. Trustees have various duties and powers which are given to them either by the general law, the Trust deed (or Will) or a combination of both. It is essential that a Trustee understands the duties imposed on him and the powers available.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">To read our free guide of these duties <a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/9_Factsheet - Trustees responsibilities.doc?1300882723" target="_blank">click here</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This can be quite a demanding role and you should know what&rsquo;s involved before agreeing to become a trustee.</p>', '2010-11-15 10:58:00', '2011-03-23 15:50:10', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>We can involve Independent Financial Advisers in our discussions at no extra cost to you</p>\r\n<p>Just ask</p>', '77_iStock_000005896679XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 115487, '2011-03-04 16:24:31', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Trusts.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 57223, '2011-01-11 11:53:36', 'Trusts', '', '', 'Trusts', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69, 'Probate and Estates', 'probate_and_estates', 'Expert Probate Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 69, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Here for you and your family</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Losing a loved one is one of the most difficult times in our lives and now more than ever you need to know you are working with people who understand your situation and can advise you of the best way to proceed.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Banner Jones Probate team in Sheffield can assist you in administering the&nbsp;estate and can provide the advice and support&nbsp;that you need.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you have been appointed as someone&rsquo;s executor, it is often difficult at this distressing time to know what to do first.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Briefly, the steps you need to take initially are:-</p>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>Find the Will</li>\r\n<li>Register the death</li>\r\n<li>Arrange the funeral</li>\r\n<li>Secure the deceased&rsquo;s property</li>\r\n<li>Collect together all the paperwork you can find</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Alternatively click here to read our&nbsp;<a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/6_What to do when someone dies FD version.pdf?1300810419" target="_blank">free guide</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information on Probate and Estates, or to arrange an appointment with our expert soilicitors, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:58:16', '2015-07-22 11:20:10', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'Fixed Fee Probate Available Now', '108_iStock_000013859617XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 98164, '2011-03-04 16:22:40', 'fixed fee probate solicitor chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'ProbateAndEstates.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 69792, '2011-01-28 16:21:51', 'Probate and Estates', '', '', 'Probate and Estates', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '<p>We can help you locate a Will&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Banner Jones are members of Certainty, a national Will register</p>', '', '', '170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 44954, '2012-06-12 12:31:37', 'Probate solicitor chesterfield', 0, '', '', ''),
(70, 'Services for the Elderly', 'services_for_the_elderly', 'Services for the Elderly', 70, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: left;">Here for you in later life</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We know that when faced with sorting out your parent''s affairs (or indeed your own) it can seem like quite a daunting task, after all how do you know you&rsquo;re doing the right thing for them? Banner Jones specialise in advising families in what types of things they can look at to make their elderly parent&rsquo;s future secure. With expert advice and careful planning you can make sure that their finances are protected from things such as care fees.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Some of the things you will want to think about are:</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: left;">\r\n<li>Making sure they have an up to date Will</li>\r\n<li>Creating a <a href="../../../page/lasting-power-of-attorney">lasting power of attorney</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/long-term-care">Long term care</a> planning to ensure their assets are protected</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you would like to speak to a solicitor then please contact us to make an appointment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:58:33', '2015-02-10 15:52:12', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Do your parents want you to look after everything for them?&nbsp;&nbsp;You can take control of their finances through a&nbsp;Lasting Power of Attorney.</p>\r\n<p>Sort it today</p>', '103_iStock_000012395773XSmall (1).jpg', 'image/jpeg', 202247, '2011-03-04 16:25:49', 'Lasting power of attorney solicitor chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'ServicesForTheElderly.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 60178, '2011-01-13 14:54:21', 'Services for the Elderly', '', '', 'Services for the Elderly', '/page/lasting-power-of-attorney', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '<p>Register your Will on a national database today, for FREE</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now included in the price of our Wills</p>', '/page/lasting-power-of-attorney', '', '170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 44954, '2012-06-12 12:30:14', 'lasting power of attorney solicitor chesterfield', 0, '', '', '');
