(71, 'Long Term Care', 'long_term_care_planning', 'Long Term Care Fees', 71, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: left;">We can help you to protect your assets</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As people live longer, more and more of us face the possibility of going into residential care. This costs on average around &pound;450 per week which means that the money you worked so hard for all your life can soon be eaten away. There are ways to preserve your assets and that&rsquo;s where we can help.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If your total assets (usually including the value of your home) exceed &pound;23,250&nbsp;&nbsp;then you will have to pay the care fees yourself, until your assets fall below that level (when the local authority will step in and contribute some of the cost). Certain assets are disregarded (see below) but the best way to prevent all your assets being used up by long term care fees is to come and see us at an early stage.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We specialise in Lifetime Planning &ndash; that is, we help people of all ages plan their future. We work closely with other professionals and the local authority to help people achieve their goals and to make sure there are no nasty surprises along the way.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">So how can we make sure you hang on to your assets?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>1.&nbsp;&nbsp; NHS funding</strong><br />The NHS has to fund all or part of the cost of care in some circumstances. We can explain this in detail and liaise with the NHS funding authorities on your behalf.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>2.&nbsp; Make use of disregarded property</strong><br />Some types of assets are disregarded by the local authority when assessing your capital. This includes the value of your home if your partner, a relative over 60 or a relative under 60 who is mentally or physically disabled still lives there when you go into care. It also includes personal belongings, such as jewellery or cars. If you wish to rely on any property being disregarded it is <span style="text-decoration: underline;">vital</span> that you talk to us first, to make sure that it complies with the rules.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>3.&nbsp; Give away an asset</strong><br /><strong>WARNING: </strong>You cannot just give away an asset for these purposes. If you give something away and one of your reasons for doing so is to avoid care fees, the &ldquo;notional capital&rdquo; rules mean that you will be assessed as still owning that asset even after you give it away. You<strong> MUST</strong> see a solicitor before giving any assets away &ndash; however large or small. We can also tell you if there are any unforeseen tax or other implications of giving things away.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We recommend that you come to us as soon as you retire &ndash; or even earlier. We can then discuss giving assets away in the context of a long term plan. We can advise on types of trust available to you or alternatives to giving away the asset.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>4.&nbsp; Financial planning</strong><br />We work closely with independent financial advisers who specialise in long term care fees planning. There are many different products available, from bonds to insurance policies, which can help to preserve your assets. We would be happy to introduce you to a financial adviser and arrange a 3-way meeting with you, them and us. That way you know that your panel of experts are all working together in your best interests.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:58:54', '2015-03-19 11:45:17', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>We work with Independent Financial Advisors with specialist care planning&nbsp;qualifications.</p>\r\n<p>This ensures you get&nbsp;a complete package of advice.</p>\r\n<p>For a joint meeting call us today</p>', '108_iStock_000013859617XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 98164, '2011-03-04 16:35:40', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'LongTermCare.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 54456, '2010-12-22 10:09:58', 'Long-term Care Planning', '', '', 'Long-term Care Planning', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', ''),
(72, 'Residential Care Appeals', 'residential_care_appeals', 'Care Fee Appeals', 72, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;">You could be paying too much</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Did you know that if you or a relative need NURSING care, as opposed to PERSONAL care, then the care will paid for by the NHS? No means testing, no cost to you at all &ndash; no matter how much money you have,&nbsp;your care will be FREE.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Did you also know that if you or a relative have been wrongly assessed as having to pay for care then you can&nbsp;challenge it and may receive a rebate from the NHS? Sadly, many people are wrongly assessed and are asked to pay for their care when it should be free of charge. Is your relative one of them?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our specialist team are experienced in challenging care funding decisions and have successfully recovered thousands of pounds for our clients. If you believe you or a relative have been wrongly assessed then speak to us straight away.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You won&rsquo;t even have to pay us unless the challenge is successful.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>', '2010-11-15 10:59:13', '2011-11-29 15:33:42', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Have you reviewed your Will in the last five years?</p>\r\n<p>We can help even if your Will was not written by Banner Jones</p>', '94_iStock_000009588868XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 47717, '2011-04-14 15:40:12', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'ResidentialCareAppeals.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 55518, '2011-01-14 17:14:12', 'Residential Care Appeals', '', '', 'Residential Care Appeals', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(74, 'Retirement Planning', 'retirement_planning', 'Retirement Planning', 74, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: left;">Planning for your future</h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">We''re with you every step of the way&hellip;</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As you approach retirement age you may want to start thinking about getting your financial affairs in order and making them as tax efficient as possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We can advise you about everything from writing a tax efficient Will to setting up trusts for your Children.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We know there is alot to consider and you may not know where to start. With this in mind&nbsp;we have developed a <strong>Later Life Planning Consultation</strong> specifically for this purpose.&nbsp; In an hours private consultation you will be able to discuss your circumstances with an experienced solicitor who will then advise you on the best course of action to suit your needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the hour you can discuss things such as:</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: left;">\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/retirement-planning-wills" target="_blank">Wills</a> and <a href="../../../page/retirement-planning-wills" target="_blank">Trusts</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/inheritance-tax" target="_blank">Inheritance Tax</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/long-term-care-retirement-" target="_blank">Care Fees Planning</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/lasting-power-of-attorney" target="_blank">Lasting Powers of Attorney</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We can even discuss funeral plans with you if required.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Following the consultation you will receive a comprehensive advice letter which will outline the recommended course of action for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please be reassured that there&nbsp;is&nbsp;no obligation to then undertake the work with Banner Jones.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6307</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:59:57', '2015-06-24 10:10:09', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>NEW</p>\r\n<p>Later Life Planning Consultation</p>\r\n<p>One hours private consultation with an experienced solicitor who will advise you on how to plan for your future</p>', '75_iStock_000005717962XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 204931, '2011-11-29 14:30:27', 'Retirement planning solicitor', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'RetirementPlanning.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 58385, '2011-01-11 11:53:19', 'Retirement Planning', '', '', 'Retirement Planning', '', '', 9, 'family_highlight', 'All of our Wills now include FREE registration&nbsp;', '', '', '170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 44954, '2012-06-12 12:20:22', 'wills solicitor chesterfield and sheffield', 0, '', '', ''),
(75, 'Defence Representation', 'derence_representation', 'Defence Representation', 75, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '', '2010-11-15 11:00:20', '2011-01-21 15:40:46', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'DefenceRepresentation.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 42487, '2010-12-22 09:41:54', 'Defence Representation', '', '', 'Defence Representation', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(76, 'Road Traffic Offences', 'road_traffic_offences', 'Motoring Offences', 76, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">With ever advancing technology constantly monitoring our driving, more and more people are finding themselves charged with Road Traffic Offences. Whether it&rsquo;s exceeding the speed limit or one of the many other offences, they all attract penalties which can quite often&nbsp; lead to significant fines, the endorsement of points on driving licences and ultimately the loss of a licence.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For some people losing their licence may mean losing their job and have other disastrous consequences. Our specialist Motoring Law Team in Chesterfield&nbsp;are experienced in defending or mitigating charges and penalties, often with the result that a driving ban is avoided.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our specialist Motoring Law team can provide advice and guidance in all motoring matters including:</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>Speeding offences</li>\r\n<li>Driving under the influence of drugs and or alcohol</li>\r\n<li>Dangerous and careless driving</li>\r\n<li>Failing to comply with traffic signals</li>\r\n<li>Defective vehicles</li>\r\n<li>Driving without insurance</li>\r\n<li>Driving whilst disqualified</li>\r\n<li>Using mobile phones</li>\r\n<li>Failing to provide information/stop after an accident</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you need fast, reliable and professional advice on how to defend a Road Traffic charge and perhaps avoid conviction or disqualification please contact us. There are instances where challenges can be made but it is crucial that you take legal advice before taking any other action.', '2010-11-15 11:00:39', '2013-05-01 15:45:57', '', '', 1, 2, 1, '2013-05-01 15:45:57', 1, 0, '<p>If you&nbsp;are being prosecuted for a&nbsp;road traffic offence&nbsp;contact us to see if we can help you.</p>\r\n<p>We could save your licence!</p>', '107_iStock_000013404152XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 42987, '2011-04-14 15:57:04', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'RoadTrafficOffences.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 35581, '2010-12-22 10:13:37', 'Road Traffic Offences', '', '', 'Road Traffic Offences', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(77, 'Public Order Offences', 'public_order_offences', 'Public Order Offences', 77, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', 'TEXT NEEDED or we hide the page?', '2010-11-15 11:00:54', '2011-03-01 15:42:54', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'PublicOrderOffences.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 44778, '2010-12-22 10:12:16', 'Public Order Offences', '', '', 'Public Order Offences', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
