(117, 'Discrimination', 'discrimination', 'We''re on your side', 115, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Sex, race, disability, age..&nbsp; the list of grounds for discrimination claims increases all the time so we know you need to&nbsp;feel confident that you have someone to turn to for the latest advice when you need it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you are an employee and feel discriminated against, we can assess your situation and provide sound advice as to whether you have a claim.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can ensure that you comply with the correct statutory grievance procedures so that you do not endanger the out come of your case through mistakes in the process.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you are an employer we can provide advice to ensure that you are not guilty of discrimination.</p>', '2011-01-27 14:25:13', '2014-02-12 14:12:00', '', '', 1, 5, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Relocating due to work?</p>\r\n<p>We can help</p>', '43_hand and keys.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 53480, '2011-04-14 15:34:46', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Discrimination.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 43543, '2011-01-27 14:26:37', 'Discrimination', '', '', 'Discrimination', '/page/residential-property', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(118, 'Maternity and Paternity Rights', 'maternity_and_paternity_rights', 'Growing your family?', 116, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">If you are about to add a new member to your family, congratulations! As a new parent you will be interested to know what you rights are with regards to time off work and indeed returning to work when the time comes.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can advise on the basic rights relating to maternity including:</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>the right not to be dismissed because of pregnancy or childbirth</li>\r\n<li>the right time off for ante-natal care</li>\r\n<li>the right to alternative work, or pay during suspension because of maternity</li>\r\n<li>the right to maternity leave</li>\r\n<li>the right to maternity pay</li>\r\n<li>the right to return to work after maternity leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Parternity rights are another area of employment law in which we advise employees including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">statutory paternity pay</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">qualifying period of employment</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">obligation to give advance notification to employer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Click here for a summary of the recent changes to <a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/10_paternity leave from 3 April 2011.doc?1300984411" target="_blank">Paternity rights</a>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-01-27 14:27:28', '2014-02-12 14:12:53', '', '', 1, 5, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Who will look after your child in the event of the unthinkable ever happening?</p>\r\n<p>Make sure you have your say, write a Will today</p>', '34_Family Image.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 276475, '2011-02-28 15:04:32', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'MaternityAndPaternityRights.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 43126, '2011-01-27 14:27:54', 'Maternity and Paternity Rights', '', '', 'Maternity and Paternity Rights', '/page/making-a-will', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(119, 'Unfair Dismissal', 'unfair_dismissal', 'Unfairly treated?', 117, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Losing your job due&nbsp;and being&nbsp;involved in an unfair dismissal claim can be very stressful and that''s why&nbsp;we will take you through the process step by step.&nbsp; If you are&nbsp;contemplating employment tribunal proceedings you will benefit from our expert advice. It is essential to be guided through the correct procedural steps before making an unfair dismissal claim to an Employment Tribunal. We can ensure you understand the&nbsp;process and help you avoid any pitfalls.</p>\r\nWe will not only advise you on the merits of the case but also on its potential costs and cost benefits. We will be upfront and tell you if we think your case is likely to succeed which will help with your decision to take the claim forward.', '2011-01-27 14:28:29', '2014-02-12 14:13:41', '', '', 1, 5, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Relocating due to work?</p>\r\n<p>We can help</p>', '69_iStock_000003465599XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 245782, '2011-04-14 15:36:16', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'UnfairDismissal.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 48317, '2011-01-27 14:28:50', 'Unfair Dismissal', '', '', 'Unfair Dismissal', '/page/residential-property', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(120, 'Redundancy', 'redundancy', 'Will it happen to me?', 118, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Redundancy is something we hear all too much about at the moment, but it is an unfortunate fact that&nbsp;most people will go through it&nbsp;at least once in their working life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you are facing redundancy at the moment&nbsp;Banner&nbsp;Jones can&nbsp;help you make sure that your rights as an employee are being dealt with in the correct manner.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We are here to take you through it step by step and can advise you of your rights including</p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>Your redundancy payment</li>\r\n<li>Time off for looking for another job</li>\r\n<li>The selection procedure and whether it was fair</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If we feel you have a case against your employer we will guide you through the tribunal process and give you an honest opinion of the likely outcome.</p>', '2011-01-27 14:29:15', '2014-02-12 14:14:23', '', '', 1, 5, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Family circumstances changing?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You should review your Will</p>', '34_Family Image.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 276475, '2011-02-28 15:27:50', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Redundancy.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 47025, '2011-01-27 14:29:35', 'Redundancy', '', '', 'Redundancy', '/page/making-a-will', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(122, 'Videos', 'videos', 'Videos', 120, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', NULL, '2011-02-08 11:59:23', '2011-02-08 11:59:23', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(123, 'Management Structure', 'management_structure', 'Management Structure', 121, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Banner Jones is managed by a board of five executive directors with designated roles covering amongst other things: finance, business development, marketing, IT, HR and accounts.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Each executive board member is appointed as the representative of one or more of the company''s various departments so that each department is always represented at&nbsp; executive board meetings.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Executive board members are appointed by election in accordance with the company''s shareholder agreement.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The current executive board members are:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="../../../team_members/32">Robert Banner</a>: Finance</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../team_members/37">Simon Wright</a>&nbsp;: Marketing, IT</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../team_members/36">Chris Sellars</a>: &nbsp;Business Development, HR</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../team_members/39">Stephen Gordon</a>: Training</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../team_members/66" target="_blank">Mark Bilton</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-02-16 15:46:35', '2013-11-18 12:16:46', '', '', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(124, 'Legal Costing', 'legal_costing_', 'Legal Costing', 122, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>Our&nbsp;team of Costs Specialists represent clients in all types&nbsp;of&nbsp;costs proceedings.</p>\r\n<p>Our aim is to maximise the recovery of costs&nbsp;in cases where an order for costs is made in the client''s favour or where an order for&nbsp;costs is made against the client to&nbsp;reduce the level of costs payable.</p>\r\n<p>Our team has over&nbsp;40 years experience in Costs law, specialising in Publicly funded and Civil Litigation costs, drafting Bills of costs and Replies and negotiating costs to settlement. This includes brain injury cases valued up to &pound;3.2 million.</p>\r\n<p>The services we provide include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Preparation of Cost Budgets</li>\r\n<li>Preparation&nbsp;of schedules of costs and subsequent negotiation</li>\r\n<li>Preparation of detailed bills of costs for assessment at court</li>\r\n<li>Preparation of Points of Dispute to the Bill of Costs</li>\r\n<li>Preparation of Replies to Points of Dispute along with subsequent negotiation.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>In the event that agreement cannot be reach&nbsp;without recourse to the court we will arrange for Costs Counsel to&nbsp;attend&nbsp;at the Detailed Assessment hearing.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>For any legal costs related advice or enquiries, contact our specialist Legal Costing team on&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span>*&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:Costing@bannerjones.co.uk">costing@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></strong>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">LEGAL AID COSTS</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">FAMILY </span></p>\r\n<p>Claim 1 &amp; 1A&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6% of profit costs &ndash; minimum charge &pound;50 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Detailed bill &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pre 01.07.08 certificates - 6% of profit costs &ndash; minimum charge &pound;90 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Post 01.07.08 certificates &ndash; Prescribed rates (claimed in bill limited to 6%)</p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">CARE </span></p>\r\n<p>Claim 1A &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6% of profit costs</p>\r\n<p>Detailed bill&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pre 01.10.07 &ndash; 6% of profit costs &ndash; minimum charge &pound;100 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Post 01.10.07 - Prescribed rates (claimed in bill limited to 6%) save where case not exceptional 6% of profit costs</p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">CIVIL </span></p>\r\n<p>Claim 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6% of profit costs &ndash; minimum charge &pound;50 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Detailed bill&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prescribed rates (claimed in bill limited to 6%)</p>\r\n<p>Legal aid assessment certificates - &pound;25 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>High costs case plans &ndash; prescribed rates (claimed in bill limited to 6%)</p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">CRIME</span></p>\r\n<p>Litigator fee claims (LF1) - &pound;30 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Litigator fee appeals (LF2) - &pound;20 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Advocacy fee claims (AF1) - &pound;30 &nbsp;+ VAT</p>\r\n<p>Assessed bills (5144) &ndash; 6% of profit costs &ndash; minimum charge of &pound;50 + VAT</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">LITIGATION COSTS</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Allocation and listing questionnaire estimates of costs</p>\r\n<p>N260 summary assessment schedule of costs</p>\r\n<p>Schedule of costs for negotiation</p>\r\n<p>Detailed bills of costs for assessment</p>\r\n<p>Request for default costs certificates</p>\r\n<p>Points of dispute to bill of costs</p>\r\n<p>Replies to points of dispute</p>\r\n<p>Negotiation and formulating part 47 offers</p>\r\n<p>Brief to costs counsel</p>\r\n<p>The above work is undertaken at SCCO guideline rates for the experience of the fee earner instructed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We can offer our services on a discounted CCFA so to limit your costs to those that are recovered from the opponent or &pound;100 per hour plus VAT where your costs are not recoverable from the opponent.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">COURT OF PROTECTION COSTS</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Short form bills - &pound;100 + VAT</p>\r\n<p>Detailed bill for provisional assessment &ndash; (Grade C SCCO Guideline rates as claimed in bill)<strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-02-17 16:36:46', '2015-03-31 11:48:28', '', '', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Our Legal Costing Team</p>\r\n<p>Kerry Anderson</p>\r\n<p>Debbie Barker</p>', 'costing group.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 372273, '2014-10-15 13:22:34', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', 'http://www.bannerjones.co.uk/team_members?team_category=18', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', ''),
(125, 'Fixed Fee Promise', 'fixed_fee_promise', 'Fixed Fee Promise', 123, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p><span style="color: #000000;">Our Fixed Fee Promise means that where we can, we''ll fix your fee upfront if you''d prefer.&nbsp; This will allow you to budget as you''ll know exactly what your final bill will be. Refreshing?</span></p>\r\n<p>The areas where we can fix your fee are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wills</li>\r\n<li>Probate. Some solicitors charge a % of the estate, we''ll fix the fee</li>\r\n<li>Lasting Powers of Attorney</li>\r\n<li>Conveyancing. The fee is fixed based on the property value</li>\r\n<li>Divorce</li>\r\n<li>Matrimonial financial matters</li>\r\n<li>Matrimonial children matters</li>\r\n<li>Dispute Resolution</li>\r\n<li>Landlord and Tenant Fixed Fee Assist</li>\r\n<li>Employment </li>\r\n<li>Debt Recovery </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-02-21 16:38:03', '2015-04-29 14:43:31', '', '', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Divorce from &pound;350+vat</p>\r\n<p>Contact us for more information</p>', '90_iStock_000009024892XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 83862, '2013-02-19 11:48:56', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, ''),
(126, 'Fixed Fee Divorce', 'fixed_fee_divorce', 'Fixed Fee Divorce', 124, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>A fresh way to look at relationship breakdown</h2>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones we know that everyone''s circumstances are different and that some clients may require more support than others.&nbsp; By working with our clients and understanding their needs we&rsquo;ve been able to develop two fixed fee divorce packages which give you the choice of how you want your divorce to be managed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>We can offer our fixed fee divorce packages in all of our offices across Chesterfield&nbsp;and Sheffield giving you even more flexibility.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>1. Forms&nbsp;Assist &pound;350 +VAT</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Forms Assist gives you the&nbsp;flexibility and control to&nbsp;manage the process yourself, but with the added reassurance that all of the forms you need will be provided fully completed and ready for you to simply lodge with the Court.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We will send you all of the forms by e-mail or post (whichever you prefer), together with a comprehensive guide on how to progress the proceedings. Be reassured however that we''ll be there for you every step of the way as you will be given a contact for e-mail and phone support.</p>\r\n<h2>What&rsquo;s included?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>No meeting required, details taken over the phone</li>\r\n<li>All the forms you need for Court,&nbsp; fully completed and checked by us</li>\r\n<li>A comprehensive guide as to how to lodge the forms with the Court</li>\r\n<li>A contact number/e-mail &nbsp;for a solicitor who can advise you at any stage along the way</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>2. Complete Assist &pound;500 +VAT</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Complete Assist may be more suited to you if your circumstances are slightly more complex and you do not want the inconvenience and responsibility of dealing with the Court yourself.&nbsp; Complete Assist gives you the reassurance that your dedicated solicitor will file all of the forms on your behalf and deal with any correspondence from the Court, whilst keeping you up to date with progress along the way.</p>\r\n<h2>What&rsquo;s included?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Face to Face meeting with your solicitor to discuss the case</li>\r\n<li>All forms fully completed and lodged with the Court on your behalf</li>\r\n<li>Regular contact from your solicitor who will update you on the progress of the case</li>\r\n<li>All Court correspondence dealt with on your behalf</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;<strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p><strong>1. What is not covered in the fixed fee?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The quotes are exclusive of vat, any Court fees or other disbursements such as swear fees. Expert reports, valuations, process server fees and any barrister&rsquo;s fees are also not covered. However, we will try and obtain fixed quotes for any work undertaken on your behalf prior to the work being carried out. The Forms Assist package cost does not include going on the Court record as acting, or entering into correspondence with court.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2. What additional work is not covered?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The cost of acquiring a replacement marriage certificate </li>\r\n<li>Any advice in relation to property, finances, children or domestic violence </li>\r\n<li>Any advice if the divorce is defended, the petition requires amendment after being issued by the Court or a cross petition is filed </li>\r\n<li>Any cases which need to be issued outside of England and Wales or a divorce where one, or both of the parties lives abroad </li>\r\n<li>Enquiry agents fees </li>\r\n<li>Advice in relation to pursuing or enforcing a costs award </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If any of these additional items are required, please be assured we are here to help you.&nbsp; Please get in touch and we can agree in advance how much any additional costs will be.</p>\r\n<p><strong>3. Do I have to pay it all at once?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ideally, yes. However, we will consider each case on it&rsquo;s merits and will consider standing orders for an agreed period of time. We can also help you in obtaining a loan to cover your legal fees.</p>\r\n<p><strong>4. What if the case settles before the end of the fixed price stage?</strong></p>\r\n<p>If your case settles up to or including the stage we have agreed the fixed price for, then the full amount is due.</p>\r\n<p><strong>5. What if my case goes beyond the agreed fixed price stage?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Matters that do not complete or settle before or at the conclusion of the agreed stage will revert to our normal hourly charging rates or a new fixed price can be agreed to the next level of the case.</p>\r\n<p><strong>6. Are there any circumstances that Banner Jones will look to recover fees over and above the fixed price?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The fixed prices are based upon the average cost of a similar case and with the information know to us at the time the fee is agreed. If however, your matter is substantially more involved or complicated than anticipated or if unexpected applications of work is required that was not anticipated at the time the fee was agreed then we reserve the right to either re-negotiate the level of the fee or to revert to our normal hourly charging rates for future work.</p>', '2011-02-25 14:45:39', '2014-02-12 14:17:09', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>If your family circumstances are changing you&nbsp;should update your Will</p>\r\n<p>Contact us now</p>', '49_wom with baby.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 185944, '2011-05-19 15:21:34', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', NULL, NULL),
(127, 'Divorce and Separation', 'divorce_and_seperation', 'Can''t take any more?', 49, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>Need to get out of your relationship? You are probably worrying about where you are going to live, whether you''ll keep your children and how much money you will have. Don''t worry we are here to help you with all the legal issues that arise when relationships break up. Whether you are married, or have been living with your partner, our experienced team will advise you on resolving these&nbsp;issues and help you get the best outcome to suit your needs.</p>\r\n<p>Many of our clients also worry about going to court when they come to see us, but be assured that there are several options available that will avoid you going to court. Collaborative law is one of the modern approaches to family breakdown and has been labelled as a &ldquo;good&rdquo; divorce as you agree from the outset that you will not go to court.</p>\r\n<p>Some couples are able to resolve their situation amicably through <a href="../../../page/mediation">Mediation</a>. Could this be right for you?</p>\r\n<h2>Start the ball rolling now with our New Fixed Fee Online Packages</h2>\r\n<h3>1. DIY Divorce - &pound;100 plus VAT</h3>\r\n<p>For some people with fairly straight forward circumstances a DIY divorce might be worth consideration.&nbsp; Simply pay online and the forms will be e-mailed or posted to you for completion.&nbsp; As part of the package you will also receive a guide on how to complete the forms.&nbsp; What''s included:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Blank Petition form</li>\r\n<li>A statement of arrangements for children</li>\r\n<li>An application for decree nisi</li>\r\n<li>A blank affidavit in support</li>\r\n<li>An application for decree absolute</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also receive a comprehenssive guide to completing the forms and how to manage the proceedings yourself. There will be additional fees payable to the court.</p>\r\n<p>No legal assistance is included in this package but if you do feel at any point that you would rather have support from us, you can simply upgrade to the DIY Assist package at any time.</p>\r\n<h3>2. DIY Assist - &pound; 300 plus vat</h3>\r\n<p>This package includes all of the forms you need, fully completed and ready for you to simply lodge them with the court.&nbsp; You receive all forms by e-mail or post whichever you prefer, together with guide for progressing the proceedings. You will also be given a contact for e-mail and phone support.</p>\r\n<p>You will still be required to pay any court fees in addition to the package cost and it does not include going on the court record as acting, entering in to correspondence with court.</p>\r\n<h3>3. Complete Assist - &pound;500 plus vat</h3>\r\n<p>This package gives you the reassurance of a dedicated solicitor who will file all of the forms on your behalf and deal with any correspondence from the court.</p>\r\n<p>You will still be required to pay any court fees in addition to the package cost and it does not include going on the Court record as acting, entering in to correspondence with court.</p>\r\n<p>What work is not covered?</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The cost of acquiring a replacement marriage certificate</li>\r\n<li>Any advice in relation to property, finances, children or domestic violence</li>\r\n<li>Any advice if the divorce is defended, the petition requires amendment after being issued by the Court or a cross petition is filed</li>\r\n<li>Any cases which need to be issued outside of England and Wales or a divorce where one, or both of the parties lives abroad</li>\r\n<li>Enquiry agents fees</li>\r\n<li>Advice in relation to pursuing or enforcing a costs award</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If any of these additional items are required, please be assured we are here to help you.&nbsp; Please get in touch and we can agree in advance how much any additional costs will be.</p>\r\n<h3>Fixed Price Work</h3>\r\n<p>We understand how concerning fee guides covering a range of possible fees for work carried out on your behalf can be. Because of this, we attempt where possible to offer <strong>fixed price</strong> agreements for our family and matrimonial clients. This allows you budget for your legal fees in advance.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is included in the fixed price?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Different types of cases will have different distinct stages that we can supply a quote for. The quote is based up the likely level of fees that would be incurred by you if your case progressed up to and including that stage, (less a discount offering you a saving on your fees if your matter progresses to that point).</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is not covered?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The quotes are exclusive of vat, any court fees or other disbursements such as swear fees, expert reports or valuations and exclusive of any barrister&rsquo;s fees. However, we will try and obtain fixed quotes for any work undertaken on your behalf by a barrister prior to the work being carried out by them.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Do I have to pay it all at once?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ideally, yes. However, we will consider each case on it&rsquo;s merits and will consider standing orders for an agreed period of time. We can also help you in obtaining a loan to cover your legal fees.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What if the case settles before the end of the fixed price stage?</strong></p>\r\n<p>If your case settles up to or including the stage we have agreed the fixed price for, then the full amount is due.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What if my case goes beyond the agreed fixed price stage?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Matters that do not complete or settle before or at the conclusion of the agreed stage will revert to our normal hourly charging rates unless a new fixed price is agreed to the next level of the case.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Are there any circumstances that Banner Jones will look to recover fees over and above the fixed price?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The fixed prices are based upon the average cost of a similar case and with the information know to us at the time the fee is agreed. If however, your matter is substantially more involved or complicated than anticipated or if unexpected applications of work is required that was not anticipated at the time the fee was agreed then we reserve the right to either re-negotiate the level of the fee or to revert to our normal hourly charging rates for future work.</p>', '2010-11-15 10:34:24', '2014-02-12 14:15:28', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p><strong>Need to sell your matrimonial home? </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>We can help</strong></p>', 'house and hands.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 112532, '2011-01-28 15:18:55', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'DivorceAndSeparation.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 56028, '2011-01-13 16:16:24', 'Divorce and Separation', '', '', 'Divorce and Separation', '/page/selling', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(128, 'Commercial Property running', 'commercial_property_running', 'Commercial Premises', 125, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>Are you looking to expand your business and not sure whether to rent or buy your premises?&nbsp; Or, maybe your current lease is&nbsp;coming up for renewal and you want some advise on your options?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Our local experienced team will get to know your business and ensure that our advice is tailored to your individual needs. There will often be things to consider that you may not have even thought about.</p>\r\n<p>When looking for business premises you may be uncertain about whether to buy your premises or maybe look at leasing long term. We can talk you through the pro&rsquo;s and con&rsquo;s for each option and guide you through them step by step.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;We can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The sale and purchase of offices and retail outlets</li>\r\n<li>Acquisition requirements such as finding and funding larger business premises </li>\r\n<li>The disposal of your business and it&rsquo;s property</li>\r\n<li>The development and/or disposal of plots</li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/landlord-or-tenant-disputes">Landlord and tenant issues</a></li>\r\n<li>Granting of leases</li>\r\n<li>Tenancy agreements</li>\r\n<li>Green Leases</li>\r\n<li>Contested leases.&nbsp; Our commercial <a href="../../../page/dispute-resolution-business">dispute resolution</a> team can advise on other contentious issues arising out of commercial property</li>\r\n<li>Buying and selling commercial <a href="../../../page/property-abroad">property abroad</a></li>\r\n<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="../../../page/notary-services">Notary Services</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-02-28 11:22:00', '2014-10-29 12:50:51', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Have you thought about a Green Lease?</p>\r\n<p>Click here for more information</p>', '74_iStock_000005586398XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 201638, '2011-03-30 11:00:58', '', 'business_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'CommercialPropertyRunning.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 58552, '2011-04-05 10:38:12', 'Commercial Property running', '', '', 'Commercial Property running', '/articles/24', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/articles/24', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', ''),
(129, 'Wills', 'retirement_planning_wills', 'Making a Will', 126, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p class="Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1">Nobody want to think about the unthinkable.</p>\r\n<p class="Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1">Making a Will is often seen as a daunting prospect for a lot of people but here at Banner Jones we&rsquo;ll take you through it step by step ensuring that your Will represents everything you want it to.&nbsp; Most of our clients say it&rsquo;s such a relief to have finally done it and usually they have been putting it off for ages.</p>\r\n<h2>Why Use Banner Jones?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Highly regarded team of qualified Wills solicitors</li>\r\n<li>FREE secure Will storage for life</li>\r\n<li>We are members of the National Will Register, ''Certainty''</li>\r\n<li>Appointments not always necessary</li>\r\n<li>Quick turnaround</li>\r\n<li>Home visits available</li>\r\n<li>Witnesses provided</li>\r\n<li>We''ll give you tax advice as part of the process</li>\r\n<li>Fixed Fee Promise on all Wills</li>\r\n<li>We will cover every detail leaving you able to relax</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Not sure where to start?</h2>\r\n<p>To help get you started here are a few things to think about when preparing to write your Will.</p>\r\n<h3>Your Estate</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Make a list of everything you own and what it is worth (assets)</li>\r\n<li>Include any life insurance policies and pension assets (if not already assigned)</li>\r\n<li>Subtract any money you may owe on death, such as mortgages and loans (liabilities)</li>\r\n<li>Estimate how much your estate is likely to be (the difference between your assets and liabilities)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>The Beneficiaries</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Make a list of those whom you want to benefit, including names and addresses.&nbsp; Think about any&nbsp;wider family and friends also</li>\r\n<li>Think about who you would like to be guardians for your children and seek their approval</li>\r\n<li>Think about whether you want to leave gifts to any charities</li>\r\n<li>Make a note of who you DON''T want to benefit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Once you have all of this information you are ready to start drafting your Will</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information or help with Wills, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Wills &amp; Probate department, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2011-03-03 11:32:53', '2015-03-19 11:47:57', '', '', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Why use a solicitor to write your Will?</p>\r\n<p>Click here for our Free guide</p>', '34_Family Image.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 276475, '2011-03-03 12:12:39', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Wills.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 51009, '2011-03-03 12:12:39', 'Wills', '', '', 'Wills', '/page/making-a-will', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '<p>Register your Will today on a national database</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Included FREE in all of our Wills</p>', '/page/making-a-will', '', '170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 44954, '2012-06-12 12:33:17', '', 0, '', '', '');
