(164, 'Solicitors', 'solicitors', 'Solicitors', 158, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: small;">How&nbsp;we can&nbsp;help&nbsp;Solicitors</span></span></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can help those who are under investigation by the SRA and those facing disciplinary proceedings. Do not think that just because you are a solicitor you are best placed to deal with it yourself.&nbsp; &nbsp;We can help with responses to a case worker, adjudicator, interview with an investigator and representation before the SDT (Solicitors Disciplinary Tribunal).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We have found that early assistance can potentially pave the way to an alternative method of resolution or avert a referral to the SDT.&nbsp; It can lead to a more favourable sanction, avoid hearing costs and&nbsp;minimise fines.&nbsp; It can also help manage problems more favourably to the client and their practice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dealing with these matters alongside the daily stresses of managing a heavy case load can be intimidating especially when files and records come under the intense scrutiny&nbsp; of an SRA investigator from either the Forensic Investigations Unit or the Conduct Investigations Unit.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Common Problems include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Solicitors Accounts Rules, Reconciliations/Issues with accounting records</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Misuse of client funds/Client account shortfall/Surplus</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Documentary irregularities</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Mortgage fraud/Money laundering</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Misconduct outside of work including convictions and police cautions</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Breach of confidentiality/Inapropriate communications</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Dishonesty including theft/False insurance applications</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In our experience, especially when faced with strict deadlines or under pressure, solicitors make knee-jerk responses in interview or in writing without recourse to the files.&nbsp; This can mean wrong assumptions are made.&nbsp; Careful and robust defence is crucial if an allegation is to be challenged successfully and if there is to be a chance of avoiding referral to the SDT and the most severe of sanctions.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Help is often appropriate for those who face a review hearing after suspension or imposition of a Conditions of Practice Order.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Things to consider:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">AVOID INTERVENTION - it is rare that decisions to intervene can be overturned</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">SEEK SPECIALIST HELP- both legal and potentially from an independent forensic accountant</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">CORRECT MISTAKES - immediately upon detection</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">CO-OPERATE WITH INVESTIGATIONS- communicate in a timely manner as failure to do so can be a breach in itself</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">CHECK THE DEADLINES- do not bury your head in the sand</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">CONSIDER REFRESHER TRAINING</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For more information on the SRA and SDT <a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/37_Solicitors factsheet.pdf?1374660736" target="_blank">please read our factsheet</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="../../../team_members/52" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">For an initial discussion with no obligation please call</span></span></a></span></span></p>', '2012-01-10 09:09:57', '2013-07-25 15:22:30', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'For a confidential no obligation chat please contact Rachel today', 'Rachel buckley large.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 119154, '2013-07-22 13:39:40', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/team_members/52', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/team_members/52', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(165, 'Dentists', 'dentists', 'Dentists', 159, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/36_Dentists factsheet.pdf?1374594202" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/36_Dentists factsheet.pdf?1374594202" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/36_Dentists factsheet.pdf?1374594202" target="_blank"></a>How we can&nbsp;help Dentists</span></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: small;">We are here for Dentists, Clinical Dental Technicians, Dental Nurses, Dental Hygienists and all those registered by the General Dental Council. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: small;">We help those without MDU backing or those wishing to seek independent legal advice especially where they face a disciplinary investigation or a&nbsp;proceeding challenging their fitness to practise.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Common Scenarios&nbsp;include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Drink driving/Police investigations, convictions and cautions</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Possession of controlled drugs or failing a drug test</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Inappropriate conduct towards patients or staff</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Failing to obtain or operate without Professional Indemnity Insurance</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Breach of professional codes of practise</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Help is often appropriate for those who face a review hearing after a suspension or imposition of a Conditions of Practice Order.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can also help with disputes in the workplace including commercial disputes and contractual/commerical matters concerning surgery ownership and development.&nbsp; Our team includes <a href="../../../team_members/39" target="_blank">specialists</a>&nbsp;who can&nbsp;help.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">For more information on the GDC please <a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/36_Dentists factsheet.pdf?1374594202" target="_blank">read our factsheet</a></span><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<span style="font-size: small;">\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">For an initial no obligation discussion call today</span></p>\r\n</span>', '2012-01-10 09:16:08', '2013-07-25 15:21:35', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'For a confidential no obligation chat please contact us today', 'dentist.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 236190, '2012-02-14 11:42:20', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(166, 'Opticians', 'opticians', 'Opticians', 160, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">How we can help Opticians</span></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">We can help those facing disciplinary investigations and proceedings by the GOC, especially those&nbsp;without assistance from ABDO or other defence unions.&nbsp; We can also help those&nbsp;seeking independent legal advice.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Increasingly Optometrists are under pressure to deal with a greater numbers of examinations in a day.&nbsp; As a consequence professional standards can slip giving rise to complaints and even fitness to practise allegations.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Common scenarios include:</span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Clinical errors inlcuding failing to detect Glaucoma/Tumours or failing to make referrals</span></span></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Incorrect prescriptions</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Dishonesty including practising whilst unqualified or over-charging</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Inapropriate conduct towards patients or staff</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Deletion or falsification of records</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Drink and drug related issues</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Police investigations, convictions and cautions</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can help you through the process ensuring you understand the procedures and the application of the criteria. We can also give you an indication of the likely sanctions that could be imposed.&nbsp; Early intervention can help secure&nbsp;early case disposal or a more lenient outcome and sometimes without referral to a fitness to practise committee.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can also&nbsp;help with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Performance assessments</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Registration appeals</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Practice regulation issues</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Disputes in the workplace</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Commercial sales, aquisitions and mergers</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you are an Optician requiring a defence lawyer then please get in touch.<span style="color: #000000; font-size: small;"></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>For more information&nbsp;on the GOC </span><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/35_Opticians factsheet.pdf?1374593944" target="_blank">read our factsheet</a></p>\r\n<a href="../../../team_members/52" target="_blank"></a>', '2012-01-10 09:22:29', '2013-07-26 15:03:10', '', '', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'For a confidential no obligation chat please contact us today', 'optician.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 250489, '2012-02-14 11:43:42', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(167, 'Accountants', 'accountants', 'Accountants', 161, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Legal defence for Accountants</span></span></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">We are here to help you if you have any difficulties arising from a complaint or a conduct/ disciplinary or regulatory issue faced by you or a member of your practice, including investigations by the police the ICAEW or ACCA.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">We are specialists in dealing with a broad range of cases from complex and high value frauds to isolated incidents of misconduct within or outside of work.</span></span></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Misconduct</span></span></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Professional accountants are expected to observe proper standards of professional conduct. They are bound by their regime of regulatory standards and code of conduct.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Disciplinary action</span> may be taken against members, firms and registered students where there is evidence of a sufficiently serious failure to observe those standards. In addition, certain non-members (such as partners in mixed practices) expressly agree to be bound by and be subject to a disciplinary regime and consequently may also be disciplined. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Not all errors made by accountants automatically attract disciplinary action. If a member has given advice which in hindsight turns out to have been flawed, and as a result of which loss has been suffered, this is primarily a matter for the firm''s professional indemnity insurers. However, disciplinary action may be appropriate if errors are of such frequency or magnitude as to signify a lack of professional competence. Whether you should make a claim against the firm''s insurance policy is a matter for discussion with your legal representative. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Disciplinary Committee/ ICAEW Investigation Committee</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Hearings are generally conducted in public, meaning that anyone may attend, including you, the member and the press. Furthermore, once a complaint is received, it may decide to proceed with its&nbsp;investigation, despite a later request&nbsp; that it may be withdrawn. </span></span></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Sanctions</span></span></span></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">These can include heavy fines and costs orders and in most serious cases removal of professional status.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">As regulation of the industry tightens complaints particularly regarding fees and professional services can become ever more frequent and costly in time and resources for your business.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Practical and timely advice is essential. Let us take the strain and let you focus on your workload. We can assist with drafting representations or full representation on your behalf whether in the early stages of an investigation or beyond.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a href="../../../team_members/52" target="_blank">\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="color: #000000;">Call us now for an initial discussion with no obligation</span></span></p>\r\n</a></span></span>', '2012-01-10 09:38:50', '2013-07-16 14:33:18', '', '', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'For a confidential no obligation chat please contact us today', '108_iStock_000013859617XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 98164, '2012-02-14 11:45:19', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(169, 'Contact', 'custody', 'Children | Family Law Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones', 163, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>I''ll be fine... but what about the kids?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Your children are the most important people in your life and you want to do what is best for them. But sometimes you can&rsquo;t see any way out of a matrimonial problem. Sometimes you feel as though the only solutions are going to be too expensive. Sometimes you feel any solution will be slanted against you because you have been at home looking after the children.&nbsp; You need help, reassurance and advice.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">With over 150 years of matrimonial experience within our department,&nbsp; we have Solicitors dealing with cases covering issues such as contact and residence for parents and the wider family.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">We have a wide range of skills (as well as experience) and can offer flexible solutions to suit your needs. We use various methods including the non Court based processes such as Collaborative Law and Mediation, as well as the more traditional route of helping you through the Court process. The best way to protect your kids is to not to involve them in expensive, ill-informed court battles.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Take some time to find out more from about <a href="../../../page/children" target="_blank"><em>Children issues,</em></a><em> <a href="../../../page/mediation" target="_blank">mediation</a>, <a href="../../../page/divorce-and-separation" target="_blank">divorce and separation</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;and <a href="../../../page/collaborative-law" target="_blank">Collaborative law</a></em>. </span></p>\r\n<h2><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">We can offer you a fixed fee initial interview which includes a free half an hour, so don&rsquo;t sit and worry unne</span><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">cessarily, call us today and let us help.</span></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</h2>', '2012-02-13 12:43:09', '2015-07-22 10:40:10', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'Fixed Free Interview Including FREE Half Hour', '158_woman and child.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 274596, '2012-02-13 12:44:36', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Family Law Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>'),
(170, 'Protecting your assets', 'protecting_your_assets', 'Protecting Your Assets', 164, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Specialists in protecting your assets in complex divorce proceedings</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Sometimes you can&rsquo;t see any way out of a matrimonial problem. Sometimes you feel as though the only solutions are going to be too expensive. Sometimes you feel any solution will be slanted against you because you have been the main breadwinner.&nbsp; You need help, reassurance and advice.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">With over 150 years of matrimonial experience within our department,&nbsp; we have Solicitors dealing with cases including lottery winners to land owners, business leaders to professional footballers.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We have a wide range of skills (as well as experience) and can offer flexible solutions to suit your needs. One of the best ways to protect your assets is to not to waste them on expensive, ill-informed Court battles.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We can help you avoid Court if this suits you, using methods such as &nbsp;the non Court based Collaborative Law and Mediation, however if preferred we can guide you through the&nbsp; more traditional Court process. Whichever method you decide to use we will be with you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Take some time to find out more from about our <a href="../../../page/fixed-fee-divorce" target="_blank">fixed fee divorce</a>, <a href="../../../page/financial-settlements" target="_blank">financial settlements</a>, <a href="../../../page/complex-divorce" target="_blank">complex divorce </a>and <a href="../../../page/collaborative-law" target="_blank">Collaborative law</a>.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">We can offer you a fixed fee initial interview which includes a free half an hour, so don&rsquo;t sit with your head in your hands, call us today and let us help.</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-02-13 12:46:40', '2014-02-12 14:20:25', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'Fixed Fee Interview Including FREE Half Hour', 'man head on bar.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 383055, '2012-02-13 12:48:38', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', 5, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(171, 'Vetinary Surgeons', 'vetinary_surgeons', 'Vetinary Surgeons', 165, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', NULL, '2012-02-21 15:21:08', '2012-02-21 15:47:32', NULL, NULL, 2, 2, 1, '2012-02-21 15:47:32', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(172, 'Parental Responsibility', 'parental_responsibility', 'Parental Responsibility', 166, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Parental Responsibility is the law&rsquo;s way of trying to define the responsibility and the rights that parents have to their child. Both married mums and dads have Parental Responsibility. </span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Effectively, parental responsibility provides the holder the right to be involved in the day to day management of the child''s life. Practically, the holders of parental responsibility are entitled to be given information regarding children&rsquo;s education and welfare.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Each parent can generally exercise their parental responsibility independently of the other and in a day to day situation there is normally no requirement for parents to consult with the other prior to exercising their parental responsibility. </span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">On certain important decisions it is essential that everyone with Parental Responsibility is consulted. A common example of this would be where one parent takes a child abroad maybe even just for a holiday. If there is no <em>Residence Order</em> in place, this cannot be done without the consent of the other parent/guardian. If this does happen we can help make the relevant emergency application through the Court for the return of the child or children.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">The position for unmarried parents is different. Unmarried mothers have parental responsibility for their child. An unmarried father whose name is on the birth certificate and the child was born after 1<sup>st</sup> December 2003 also has it. &nbsp;An unmarried father for a child born before 1<sup>st</sup> December 2003 can acquire parental responsibility by either:</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&bull;Entering into a parental responsibility agreement with the mother</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&bull;Obtaining an order of the Court</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&bull;Marrying the&nbsp; mother of his child</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&bull;By ensuring his name is on the birth certificate, either originally&nbsp; or by re-registration of the child&rsquo;s birth to include the father&rsquo;s name</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">If you would like more information on parental responsibility then contact us today</span></p>', '2012-02-22 15:24:01', '2014-02-12 14:20:41', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p>First 30 minutes Free</p>', '158_woman and child.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 274596, '2012-02-22 15:26:52', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(173, 'Residence Orders', 'residence_orders', 'Residence Orders', 167, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p><span style="color: #000000;">Residence orders are settled by the Court and dictate with whom the child or children should live. It is rare for a Court to separate siblings, but if it is in the children''s best interests, they will do so.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;">The Courts will now quite often make&nbsp; &ldquo;joint&rdquo; or &ldquo;shared&rdquo; residence orders, so that in effect the child or children will have two&nbsp;homes.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000;">The order can set out exactly when each child lives in each home, or it can be set out in general terms if the Court is confident that both parties can agree.</span></p>', '2012-02-22 15:27:47', '2014-02-12 14:20:42', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee interview</p>\r\n<p>First 30 minutes FREE</p>', '84_iStock_000007985661XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 174578, '2012-02-22 15:30:37', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(174, 'Contact Orders', 'contact_orders', 'Contact Orders', 168, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Contact orders settle how and when a child should have contact with the person (usually the parent) they do not live with. </span><br /><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Contact can take many forms including:</span>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">letters and emails</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">telephone contact</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">visiting contact</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">staying contact</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Where there are concerns about the level of care the adult wishing to have contact can give, the Court may order a period of supervised contact.&nbsp; This is where&nbsp; another adult is present to ensure the child or children do not come into any harm.</span><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-02-22 15:32:51', '2014-02-12 14:20:44', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p>First 30 mins FREE</p>', '80_iStock_000006952947XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 100894, '2012-02-22 15:35:50', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(175, 'Applying to Court', 'applying_to_court', 'Applying to the Court', 169, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">This is often seen as the last resort because you can only apply to the Court when you have ensured that all avenues of amicable agreement have been exhausted. It is important to remember that a Court battle can be a long drawn out series of hearings and, throughout this, your children will &nbsp;be aware of what is happening. They may have to speak to the Court welfare officer (Cafcass officer) during this time, too. </span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">The Cafcass service are instructed to make preliminary enquiries once your application is made. They will speak to&nbsp; you and the other parent before the first hearing and make written recommendations to the Court. The Cafcass officer will also be available to discuss issues with you both at the first hearing.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">If an agreement can be reached at the first hearing an order can be made, either on a final basis or on the basis that it is reviewed in the future.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">If an agreement can&rsquo;t be reached and the Cafcass has no welfare concerns for the children, then the Court will list the case for a contested hearing where each of you will be able to submit a statement setting out what you believe is best for your children. If there are welfare concerns, possibly due to historic aggression or violence, the Court will make orders to enable it to get to the bottom of what has happened and the Cafcass service will be asked to prepare a more detailed report where the children&rsquo;s wishes and feelings&nbsp; will be one of the factors that the court&nbsp; will need to consider. </span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;">Obviously if the Court have to make the finals decision on the arrangements for your children then you ability to control the final outcome has been lost. This is why the vast majority of separating parents manage to make their own arrangements outside the Court arena.</span></p>', '2012-02-22 15:37:56', '2014-02-12 14:20:46', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p>First 30 mins Free</p>', '79_iStock_000006943094XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 88506, '2012-02-22 15:40:47', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(176, 'Adoption Orders', 'adoption_orders', 'Adoption Orders', 170, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>When an Adoption Order is made, the child&rsquo;s legal status within their natural family is &nbsp;terminated and they become a full legal member of a new adoptive family.</p>\r\n<p>These orders may be &ldquo;closed&rdquo; whereby the natural family have no further involvement in the child&rsquo;s life or in some cases, it is appropriate to make an &ldquo;open&rdquo; Adoption Order, whereby there is some form of continued contact between the child and some or all members of their natural family.</p>\r\n<p>Adoption Orders aim to provide a stable family environment for a child hopefully with a successful integration into the new family life.</p>', '2012-02-22 15:42:00', '2014-02-13 11:11:11', '', '', 2, 5, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p>First 30 mins FREE</p>', '57_iStock_000000258794XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 129343, '2012-02-22 15:43:51', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(177, 'Care Proceedings', 'care_proceedings', 'Care Proceedings', 171, 0, 0, 0, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Our work with children includes care proceedings brought by the social services.&nbsp; Social services may tell you that they are going to start care proceedings, but if they do not, you will find out when you receive a notice from the court telling you when and where the first hearing will be.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The people who hold the <a href="../../../page/parental-responsibility" target="_blank">parental responsibility </a>of the child have the right to decide how a child is raised and cared for.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Generally, we represent parents and children in these proceedings but sometimes we represent grandparents or foster parents. Our approach is to focus on the welfare of the child and to help you understand how the Courts make decisions in these types of cases.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Helena Downing, Kevin Tomlinson and Diane Gunn are all on the Law Society''s Children&rsquo;s panel. Only solicitors who meet the Law Society&rsquo;s exacting accreditation requirements are permitted to join the Children Panel and represent children in public law care proceedings.&nbsp; Your skills, knowledge and experience are rigorously and independently assessed in order to achieve this accreditation status. This means that you know you are dealing with the very best .</p>', '2012-02-22 15:47:30', '2014-02-12 14:20:52', '', '', 2, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p>First 30 mins FREE</p>', '54_iStock_000001364064XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 179160, '2012-02-22 15:50:46', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(178, 'Fixed Fee', 'fixed_fee', 'Fixed Fee', 172, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', 'Content Needed', '2012-02-22 16:15:11', '2012-02-22 16:15:18', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL),
