(231, 'Drink and Drug Driving Offences ', 'drink_and_drug_driving_offences_', 'Drink and Drug Driving Solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield | Banner Jones ', 213, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h1><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Please note: From 5pm on Friday 24th April 2015 the Banner Jones Solicitors Criminal Defence department became part of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vhsfletchers.co.uk" target="_blank">VHS Fletchers Solicitors</a>.<br /><br /></strong><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">As a result, if you have a live Criminal Defence matter this has been automatically been transferred.</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><span><br /></span></strong><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">Banner Jones offer expert advice on Drink and Drug Driving Laws</span></p>\r\n<p>Driving with excess alcohol, often called &lsquo;Drink Driving&rsquo;, is one of the most common offences before the Magistrates Court. We know that the consequences of being convicted of the drink drive offence can have serious effects, not just upon yourself, but also on your family.</p>\r\n<p>We have put together a Drink Driving Maximum Penalty Guide, providing you with all the necessary information on the drink driving law, penalties, problems and the drink drive rehabilitation course. Please click below to open our guide:</p>\r\n<p><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Drink Driving Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/72_Driving Offences - Drink Driving Penalty Guide.pdf?1402499053" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/95_Driving Offences - Drink Driving Penalty Guide.pdf?1409044931" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/231/contained_images/ed0975417c33_297_Drink Driving.JPG?1402499791" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/95_Driving Offences - Drink Driving Penalty Guide.pdf?1409044931" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<p>The table below sets out the sentencing guidelines for a first time offender convicted of drink driving.</p>\r\n<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Level of Alcohol (Breath/mg)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Likely Disqualification</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p><strong>Likely other Punishment</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>36-59</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>12-16 months</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>Fine</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>60-89</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>17-22 months</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>Fine</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>9-119</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>23-28 months</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>Community Order</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>120-150+</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>29-36 months</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="205" valign="top">\r\n<p>12 weeks custody</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The consequences for failing a breath test, or having impairments, can have long term impacts upon your life, including having a criminal record, driving bans, rising insurance premiums and even loss of job.</p>\r\n<p>Therefore, it is imperative that you seek professional legal advice from a specialist drink driving solicitor so that your options are highlighted, you are fully prepared for the consequences and, importantly, made aware of the defences.</p>\r\n<h2>Drink and Drug Driving Defences</h2>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones we understand that falling foul of this law can often simply be a misjudgement of&nbsp; alcohol intake, or a timing issue, if, for example, driving the next day. Therefore we can review your detailed paperwork and offer an honest appraisal as to whether you may have a technical defence. The sentencing guidelines for the offence concentrate on the level of the alcohol reading. However, our experience from daily court appearances tells us that other factors can have a great impact on the length of driving disqualification, fine or other punishment the court sentences you to.</p>\r\n<p>We are also aware of the technical defences to the offence. Our specialist solicitors will advise you on all defences available, and your chances of success. If you have a defence, we will assist you from the outset in presenting this to the court in the best possible way.</p>\r\n<h2>Contact a specialist Drink and Drug Driving Solicitor</h2>\r\n<p>Our expert drink driving solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield are highly experienced, and will treat each case uniquely depending on your circumstances. Our drink and drug driving specialists are always on hand to provide support, as we know this can be a stressful time for our clients. We have worked on many drink and drug driving cases, and each individual receives the upmost care and consideration throughout the case.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert drink driving solicitors, please&nbsp;<strong><strong><strong>call&nbsp;<strong><a href="tel: +441246283000">01246 283000</a></strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk">chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk</a>.</strong></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong><br /></strong></strong></strong></strong></p>', '2014-02-10 14:53:43', '2015-07-22 09:09:45', 'At Banner Jones we offer expert advice on driving under the influence of drugs and alcohol. We are specialist drink and drug driving solicitors. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/95_Driving Offences - Drink Driving Penalty Guide.pdf?1409044931" target="_blank">Download Drink Driving Penalty Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/72_Driving Offences - Drink Driving Penalty Guide.pdf?1402499053" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/95_Driving Offences - Drink Driving Penalty Guide.pdf?1409044931" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/296_Drink Driving Icon.JPG?1402499014" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Drink and Drug Driving Offences ', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Driving Offences Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n'),
(232, 'Careless Driving ', 'careless_driving_', 'Careless Driving Offences| Specialist Driving Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 214, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h1><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Please note: From 5pm on Friday 24th April 2015 the Banner Jones Solicitors Criminal Defence department became part of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vhsfletchers.co.uk" target="_blank">VHS Fletchers Solicitors</a>.<br /><br /></strong><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">As a result, if you have a live Criminal Defence matter this has been automatically been transferred.</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><span><br /></span></strong><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">At Banner Jones we have a team of specialist Driving Offence Solicitors who can advise you on Careless Driving Offences</span></p>\r\n<h2>Careless Driving Guide</h2>\r\n<p>To explain the difference between inconsiderate, careless and dangerous driving, and the associated penalties and convictions, we have developed a guide to provide you with all the necessary information and advice surrounding careless driving. Please click below to read this guide:</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/86_Driving Offences - Careless Driving Guide.pdf?1408702636" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/94_Driving Offences - Careless Driving Guide.pdf?1409044884" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/232/contained_images/dfe95b99016b_336_Careless Driving Guide.jpg?1408703115" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Careless Driving Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/94_Driving Offences - Careless Driving Guide.pdf?1409044884" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<h2>Dangerous and Careless Driving</h2>\r\n<p>Often, driving without due care and attention can stem from something as simple as changing a CD, ignoring a red light or driving inappropriately fast for the road conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Careless driving, sometimes known as &ldquo;driving without due care and attention&rdquo;, means that the standard of driving falls below what would be expected of a competent and careful driver. To be convicted of the offence, the prosecution must prove to the court that you were driving below the standard expected of a competent and careful driver. It is an easy offence to commit by accident by, for example, having a momentary lapse in concentration. If your driving is held below this legal standard, it could affect your livelihood through fines, points on your license or even disqualification from driving.</p>\r\n<p>Dangerous Driving mirrors the definition above, but it must also be obvious to a competent and careful driver that the action would be dangerous. Examples include racing, inappropriate overtaking and even driving with a known medical condition which impairs driving skills. If convicted, the result could be a prison sentence and disqualification.</p>\r\n<h2>Failure to comply with traffic signals</h2>\r\n<p>This offence can often committed through an honest mistake, or a lack of concentration; however, any driver convicted of contravening a traffic signal (e.g. red lights/one way roads) will automatically be given 3 penalty points on their licence.</p>\r\n<p>In many circumstances, these cases can be very defendable based upon disproving unreliable evidence against you from fixed cameras or from a police or civilian witness that reports the behaviour.</p>\r\n<p>The penalties may not be as severe as those associated with other offences, however the impact on your license could damage insurance claims or even lead to disqualification if coupled with other offences. Therefore, expert legal advice from a respected, local firm of specialist solicitors is imperative to gain a successful defence.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h2>Failure to provide information/stop after an accident</h2>\r\n<p>These offences are actually separate, but are often charged together, and can incur harsh penalties such as points or even disqualification.</p>\r\n<p>You are guilty of failing to stop if you have an accident and do not stop and provide information. This is where complications can occur as you do not have to be directly involved in the accident.</p>\r\n<p>Often, it doesn&rsquo;t matter whose fault the accident is. You still need to stop and exchange information with those involved, or risk a penalty.</p>\r\n<p>The only exception is if you didn&rsquo;t know there was an accident, which is where Banner Jones can significantly aid your chances of a successful defence. Due to the severe sentencing powers available to the Court for these offences, expert advice and representation should be sought from the outset.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">Find out more information on Careless Driving Offences</span></p>\r\n<p>Our specialist solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield will discuss your case with you and provide an expert opinion on whether you have committed an offence or not.&nbsp; Although some offences are easy to commit, the consequences can be great.&nbsp; If the careless driving is of a particularly poor standard, you could be disqualified immediately. In other cases, you would receive penalty points on your driving licence. If you already have penalty points on your licence, this could put you at risk of being disqualified from driving as a result of being a &lsquo;totter upper&rsquo;. Please see our <a href="../../../page/totting-up" target="_blank">totter upper</a>&nbsp;section for more information.</p>\r\n<p>Our experienced driving offence team can tailor their advice and assistance to your individual needs by taking into account mitigating factors and potential defences that can support your case. If you need fast reliable and professional advice on how to defend a careless driving offence charge, and perhaps avoid conviction or disqualification, please contact one of our driving offence solicitors. There are instances where challenges can be made, but it is crucial that you take legal advice before any other action.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange your appointment with our expert driving offence solicitors, please&nbsp;<strong><strong><strong>call&nbsp;<strong><a href="tel: +441246283000">01246 283000</a></strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk">chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk</a>.</strong></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong><br /></strong></strong></strong></strong></p>', '2014-02-10 14:59:48', '2015-07-22 09:10:21', 'At Banner Jones we offer expert care and advice on careless driving offences. We have a team of expert driving offence solicitors. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/94_Driving Offences - Careless Driving Guide.pdf?1409044884" target="_blank">Download Careless Driving Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/86_Driving Offences - Careless Driving Guide.pdf?1408702636" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/94_Driving Offences - Careless Driving Guide.pdf?1409044884" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/337_Careless Driving Guide Icon.jpg?1408703124" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Careless Driving Offences ', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Driving Offences Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n'),
(233, 'Mobile Phone Driving Offences ', 'mobile_phone_driving_offences_', 'Mobile Phone Driving Offences| Specialist Driving Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 215, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h1><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Please note: From 5pm on Friday 24th April 2015 the Banner Jones Solicitors Criminal Defence department became part of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vhsfletchers.co.uk" target="_blank">VHS Fletchers Solicitors</a>.<br /><br /></strong><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">As a result, if you have a live Criminal Defence matter this has been automatically been transferred.</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><span><br /></span></strong><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">At Banner Jones we provide expert care and advice on Mobile Phone Driving Offences</span></p>\r\n<p>The use of Mobile Phones whilst driving is a relatively new development in UK law, and police traffic patrols are increasingly on the lookout for drivers committing this particular offence. Mobile phone offences can be split into 3 categories:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Use of a hand held telephone by the driver of a vehicle*</li>\r\n<li>Causing or permitting the use by the driver</li>\r\n<li>Supervising a provisional driver whilst using a telephone</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong><sub>* Importantly, use of a mobile phone includes both texting and making telephone calls.</sub></strong></p>\r\n<h2>Mobile Phone Driving Guide</h2>\r\n<p>Here at Banner Jones, we have developed a Mobile Phone Driving Guide outlining legislation, penalties as well as useful information for employees and employers:</p>\r\n<p><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Mobile Phone Driving Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/73_Driving Offences - Mobile phone driving guide.pdf?1402499904" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/96_Driving Offences - Mobile phone driving guide.pdf?1409044951" target="_blank"><img style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/233/contained_images/9bc7c3eca2a4_298_Mobile Phone Driving.JPG?1402500226" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/96_Driving Offences - Mobile phone driving guide.pdf?1409044951" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">Driving with mobile phone penalties</span></p>\r\n<p>The penalties for use in the above situations are 3 points on your drivers license, and a fine up to a maximum of &pound;1000. If you were using a mobile and were then involved in an accident, the penalties are more severe as you may be charged with careless or dangerous driving.</p>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones, our specialist motoring law team handles many mobile phone cases, providing successful defences and fast reliable advice to our clients. If you have been charged with the above offence, please contact our experienced team of solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield to get help with your defence and avoid the penalties.</p>\r\n<h2>Find out more information on mobile phone offences</h2>\r\n<p>If you need fast reliable and expert advice on mobile phone driving offences, please contact one of our experienced driving offence solicitors. We understand that this can be a stressful time for our clients. Our solicitors treat each case with care and consideration. We encourage you to seek expert legal advice if you have been charged with a mobile phone driving offence, before you take any other action.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert driving offence solicitors, please&nbsp;<strong><strong><strong>call&nbsp;<strong><a href="tel: +441246283000">01246 283000</a></strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk">chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk</a>.</strong></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong><br /></strong></strong></strong></strong></p>', '2014-02-10 15:07:28', '2015-07-22 09:10:48', 'At Banner Jones we offer expert advice on mobile phone driving offences. We have a team of expert experienced driving offence solicitors. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/96_Driving Offences - Mobile phone driving guide.pdf?1409044951" target="_blank">Download Mobile Phone Driving Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/73_Driving Offences - Mobile phone driving guide.pdf?1402499904" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/96_Driving Offences - Mobile phone driving guide.pdf?1409044951" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/299_Mobile Phone Driving Icon.JPG?1402500246" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Mobile Phone Driving Offences ', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Driving Offences Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n'),
(234, 'Road Traffic Offences ', 'road_traffic_offences_', 'Road Traffic Offences | Specialist Driving Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 216, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h1><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Please note: From 5pm on Friday 24th April 2015 the Banner Jones Solicitors Criminal Defence department became part of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vhsfletchers.co.uk" target="_blank">VHS Fletchers Solicitors</a>.<br /><br /></strong><strong style="font-family: Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">As a result, if you have a live Criminal Defence matter this has been automatically been transferred.</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><span><br /></span></strong><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">At Banner Jones we offer expert specialist advice on all matters of Driving Offences</span></p>\r\n<h2>Road Traffic Offences Penalty Points Guide</h2>\r\n<p>We have put together a guide to provide you with sufficient information on road traffic offences and the penalties that may incur:</p>\r\n<p><strong><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Road Traffic Offences'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/74_Driving Offences - Road Traffic Offences - Penalty Points Guide.pdf?1402500955" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/97_Driving Offences - Road Traffic Offences - Penalty Points Guide.pdf?1409044964" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/234/contained_images/836a1dcf91cd_300_Road Traffic Offences.JPG?1402500931" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></strong></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/97_Driving Offences - Road Traffic Offences - Penalty Points Guide.pdf?1409044964" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></strong></p>\r\n<h2>Defective Vehicles<strong>&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<p>The offence of a defective vehicle is often a result of irregular servicing, neglect to the vehicle or the driver being oblivious to the highlighted defects. Banner Jones'' specialist Motoring Law Team consists of highly skilled lawyers dedicated to providing expert legal advice to clients facing prosecution for driving defective vehicles.</p>\r\n<p>This law is in place primarily for safety reasons to the driver and all road users as the motor vehicle must meet certain standards.&nbsp; An offence is committed if your vehicle is considered unsafe for you, your passengers or the public in light of minor or major vehicle defects.</p>\r\n<p>Therefore, it is imperative the you seek professional legal advice from our specialist solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield to outline options and defences that may be available to you.</p>\r\n<p>Issues or matters that may appear simple can in fact be complex when concerning defective vehicles and our expertise will help you ensure that you fully understand your legal position, so please don''t hesitate to get in touch.</p>\r\n<h2>Driving Without Insurance</h2>\r\n<p>The Magistrates Court takes a dim view of driving without insurance because of the potential implications were you to have an uninsured accident. If you have been charged with driving without insurance, contact our specialist Motoring Law Team for advice tailored to your personal circumstances.</p>\r\n<p>Many drivers get caught out with the belief that their fully comprehensive insurance covers them to drive another vehicle owned by someone else, with their permission. Many fully comprehensive policies don&rsquo;t provide this type of cover automatically and this is a common fall for many clients.</p>\r\n<p>To be prosecuted for this offence, the police normally are able to show that a person was driving the vehicle. However, the offence itself is &ldquo;using&rdquo; the vehicle and this has a broader definition than merely driving.</p>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones, our specialist team understand the defence for driving without insurance can be a complex procedure and the sooner you gain expert advice the better. If you need fast, reliable and expert advice please don''t hesitate to contact us.</p>\r\n<h2>Driving Whilst Disqualified</h2>\r\n<p>If caught driving whilst disqualified, the offence can only be tried in the Magistrates'' Court and can carry serious penalties including prison time. &nbsp;At Banner Jones'', our specialist Motoring Law Team have numerous years of experience in handling disqualified driver claims.</p>\r\n<p>Driving whilst disqualified is a strict liability offence meaning that the prosecution only has to prove that you were in control of a motor vehicle whilst being disqualified. This also means there are only limited defences. However, we will carefully assess the evidence against you and find your available defence.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Contact a Specialist Driving Offence Solicitor</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Our expert driving offence solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield are highly experienced and will treat each case uniquely as we know each of our clients have different circumstances. Our driving offence specialists achieve solutions through confidential settlements and are always on hand to provide support as we understand this can be a stressful and worrying period due to the severe implications<strong>.</strong> We have worked on many driving offence cases and each individual receives the upmost care and consideration.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert driving offence solicitors, please&nbsp;<strong><strong><strong>call&nbsp;<strong><a href="tel: +441246283000">01246 283000</a></strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk">chesterfield@vhsfletchers.co.uk</a>.</strong></strong></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><strong><strong><br /></strong></strong></strong></strong></p>', '2014-02-10 15:19:13', '2015-07-22 09:14:30', 'At Banner Jones we offer advice on road traffic offences including driving whilst disqualified, driving without insurance and defective vehicles. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/97_Driving Offences - Road Traffic Offences - Penalty Points Guide.pdf?1409044964" target="_blank">Download Road Traffic Offences Penalty Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/74_Driving Offences - Road Traffic Offences - Penalty Points Guide.pdf?1402500955" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/97_Driving Offences - Road Traffic Offences - Penalty Points Guide.pdf?1409044964" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/301_Road Traffic Offences Icon.JPG?1402500977" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Road Traffic Offences ', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Driving Offences Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n'),
(235, 'Buying', 'buying', 'Buying a House Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 43, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Banner Jones Solicitors are experts at conveyancing </strong></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Buying a house is an exciting time for anybody but the process can be a bit daunting so that''s why we are here to offer you expert advice on&nbsp;buying a house conveyancing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Once you are a client you can keep up to date with your purchase very easily by checking your case online. Our interactive case tracking website allows you to check your progress 24/7. You will also receive a text message when a key milestone has been completed within the house conveyancing process.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We have outlined the process of buying a home in our easy to digest, downloadable guide which provides you with essential information on the 6 stages of buying a home:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/52_Buying a home process one pages.pdf?1390499682" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/235/contained_images/4e2b35a53267_350_Buying a House.JPG?1409050112" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Buying Your House Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/52_Buying a home process one pages.pdf?1390499682" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Steps to Buying a House</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The steps involved in buying a house are relatively straight forward, however, it can get more complex if there are several buyers in the chain. That is why it is even more important to instruct a solicitor if you are thinking of buying a house. The conveyancing solicitor will keep you up to date along the way as well as keeping you up to date on the buying a house process.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Use a Banner Jones expert Solicitor when Buying a House</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As a thank you for choosing Banner Jones as your solicitors for buying a house you will get our <a href="../../../page/purchase-plus" target="_blank">purchase plus package</a> absolutely free! This applies only if you are buying a house in Chesterfield or Sheffield.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you are considering the purchase of a new build house you may want to look into the new help to buy scheme which was launched in April this year. Banner Jones have already helped buyers move into properties using this scheme and we can help you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">At Banner Jones our highly trained solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield offer support and care to all of our clients. We also offer a professional approach to each case whilst also ensuring that all of our services are fully confidential. We will provide you with advice on the steps to buying a house that will help guide you through the conveyancing process.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Conveyancing solicitors, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or emai&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:32:16', '2015-07-22 10:59:35', 'At Banner Jones we are expert house conveyancing solicitor. If you are buying your house we can offer you advice and guidance on the steps involved. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Quality Guaranteed</p>\r\n<p>Call today for a quote</p>', '182_Accredited CQ_logo rgb.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 61971, '2013-03-28 15:18:29', 'Conveyancing solicitors Chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Buying.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 35258, '2010-12-22 09:35:48', 'Buying', '', '', 'Buying', '/web/contact_us', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a onclick="_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'', ''Guide'', ''Download'', ''Buying you house'']);" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/52_Buying a home process one pages.pdf?1390499682" target="_blank">Buying a Home Process Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/52_Buying a home process one pages.pdf?1390499682" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/351_Buying a House Icon.JPG?1409050395" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a onclick="_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'', ''Guide'', ''Download'', ''Buying and Selling Houses'']);" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/62_Residential Conveyancing - Buying and Selling Houses - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883544" target="_blank">Buying &amp; Selling Houses Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/62_Residential Conveyancing - Buying and Selling Houses - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883544" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/343_Buying &amp; Selling Houses Icon.JPG?1409048697" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Buying a House', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Conveyancing Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n'),
(236, 'Help to Buy Scheme', 'help_to_buy_scheme', 'Help to Buy Scheme | Conveyancing Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 185, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Banner Jones can offer help and guidance on the Help to Buy Scheme</h2>\r\n<p>We have prepared an article compiling some key information breaking down the 3 stage process of buying a home on the help to buy scheme. <strong>Click below to open this article:</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/69_Residential Conveyancing - Help to buy scheme - How to buy a help to buy home.pdf?1400502458" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/236/contained_images/9e0c9c81468c_273_Residential Conveyancing - Help to buy scheme - How to buy a help to buy home 2.png?1400502802" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Help to Buy Scheme'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/69_Residential Conveyancing - Help to buy scheme - How to buy a help to buy home.pdf?1400502458" target="_blank">Open Article</a></p>\r\n<h2>The Help to Buy Scheme explained</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Phase 1 April 2013:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The new Government <strong>help to buy scheme</strong> was introduced in April 2013 to help stimulate the housing market by providing loans of up to 20% of the purchase price on a new build home. We know that saving for an adequate deposit can be very hard for first time buyers in the current market so the loan will help to bridge the gap between what you can borrow from a mortgage lender and what you can afford as a deposit.</p>\r\n<h2>Key facts on the Help to Buy Scheme</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The loans are available on new build properties only</li>\r\n<li>It is open to both first time buyers and people who have a property to sell</li>\r\n<li>It must be the person&rsquo;s main residence. It cannot be a sublet or be a second home</li>\r\n<li>You cannot keep your existing property and let it out</li>\r\n<li>You must take out the standard first mortgage with a qualifying lender </li>\r\n<li>There is no higher income threshold</li>\r\n<li>The maximum purchase price is &pound;600,000</li>\r\n<li>The loan will be repaid on the sale of the property or after 25 years, whichever comes first. You can also make voluntary repayments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Help to Buy Home Scheme example</h2>\r\n<p>In an example where&nbsp;you purchase a &pound;200,000 home under the <strong>help to buy scheme</strong>, the agency&rsquo;s contribution of the equity loan totals &pound;40,000 or 20% of the purchase price. You will be required to produce a 5% deposit of &pound;10,000 and a mortgage of &pound;150,000.</p>\r\n<p>The equity loan is interest free for the first 5 years. After 5 years you pay a fee of 1.75% rising annually by the increase in the retail price index plus 1%. In year 6 on the previous example of &pound;40,000 this would be approximately &pound;58 a month.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">The Help to Buy Scheme process explained</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Phase 2 October 2013:</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Homebuyers can now consider whether to take advantage of the second phase of the Government''s Help to Buy scheme, brought in three months early in a bid to help revive the property market.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Phase 2&nbsp; is available to existing home-owners looking to move to any type of property, not just first-time buyers.&nbsp;The buyer must still put up at least a 5 per cent cash deposit, but the Government no longer lends actual cash to the buyer. Instead, it guarantees up to 15 per cent of the mortgage granted so that, if the borrower defaults and the property is repossessed and sold for less than the balance of the mortgage, the lender can apply directly to the Government for repayment under the guarantee.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The buyer needs to contribute a cash deposit of 5 per cent of the purchase price, and to satisfy the lender''s usual checks. The aim is to reduce the risk to lenders so that they can offer cheaper interest rates to buyers. The lender pays the Government a fee for its guarantee.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The property must be worth less than &pound;600,000, and borrowers must not own any buy-to-let properties or intend to keep the home they currently live in after the purchase.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: justify;">How to buy a help to buy home</h2>\r\n<h3><strong>Stage 1 - Application</strong></h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">An application needs to be made to the local help to buy agent. The application&nbsp;includes a Property Information Form which shows details of the proposed purchase, main mortgage, deposit and household income. The Property Information Form also confirms&nbsp;your agreement to the funds due being paid directly to the house builder.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">You will need to sign the Property Information Form with a copy of the Builders Reservation Form which must be sent to the local home buyer agent.</p>\r\n<h3>Authority to proceed</h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The local home buyer agent assesses the application and if passed they will issue an authority to proceed. This is valid for 3 months and exchange of contracts must take place within this period.</p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;<strong>Stage 2 - Exchange of Contracts</strong></h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">You will need to go through the normal&nbsp;<span style="font-size: small;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/4_buying a home process one pages.pdf?1300809818" target="_blank">conveyancing process</a>&nbsp;</span>with regard to the property but you will also need legal support with the signing of the help to buy equity loan agreement. &nbsp;Banner Jones&nbsp;can help you with this.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We will need to check that the mortgage offer, property price and available funds are consistent with the authority to proceed and request permission to exchange contracts from the local home buyer agents.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">An approval is received before contracts can be exchanged.</p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Stage 3 - Completion</strong></h3>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li>The agents pay the funds direct to the developer.</li>\r\n<li>We return confirmation of the sale to the local home buyer agent who will then register the details with the post sale home buyer agent. </li>\r\n<li>We deal with the registration of the second charge. ie, the loan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Sale of the Property</h3>\r\n<p><span style="text-align: justify;">Consent from the post sale home buyer agent is required and the agencies mortgage will only be released with their permission. Their main concern is that the sale of the property is at the correct market value and they can request an independent valuation to ensure this.</span></p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Conveyancing solicitors, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2013-06-10 11:31:18', '2015-07-22 11:03:15', 'At Banner Jones we can give you advice on the help to buy scheme and explain simply what the help to buy scheme is and how you could benefit. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'Quality Conveyancing Guaranteed', '182_Accredited CQ_logo rgb.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 61971, '2013-06-10 13:50:45', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', 9, 'family_highlight', 'For a FREE conveyancing quote call us now', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/69_Residential Conveyancing - Help to buy scheme - How to buy a help to buy home.pdf?1400502458" target="_blank">Download How to Buy a Help to Buy Home Article</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/69_Residential Conveyancing - Help to buy scheme - How to buy a help to buy home.pdf?1400502458" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/274_Residential Conveyancing - Help to buy scheme - How to buy a help to buy home graphic.png?1400502896" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Help to Buy Scheme', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Conveyancing Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n');
