(237, 'Selling', 'selling', 'Selling Your Home | Conveyancing Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 44, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Banner Jones are expert solicitors when it comes to Selling your House</h2>\r\n<p>There are many reasons why you may need to sell your house, but whatever your circumstances we&rsquo;ll be with you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p>The process behind selling your house is not complex but it&rsquo;s important to have a qualified conveyancer on your side for any unforeseen complications that can arise.</p>\r\n<p>If you are using Banner Jones to sell your house don&rsquo;t forget you can log in now to chase your case progress. Our tracking interactive site allows you to check your selling process. You will also receive a text message when a key milestone has been completed this aids with communication throughout the selling process.</p>\r\n<p><span>We have outlined the process of selling a home in our easy to digest, downloadable guide which provides you with essential information on the 6 stages of buying a home:</span></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/53_Selling a home process.pdf?1390499695" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/237/contained_images/31e220194b46_352_Selling Your House.JPG?1409050790" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Selling Your House Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/53_Selling a home process.pdf?1390499695" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">Selling your House services</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you are selling your house due to a marriage breakdown we have a specialist divorce team who may be able to give you further advice about the division of your assets</li>\r\n<li>If you are selling a house as part of a probate, again we have a specialist team who will be able to advise you and give appropriate tax advice</li>\r\n<li>If you are selling a house abroad you may need the services of a notary to legalise the signing of any documents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Selling your House advice</h2>\r\n<p>If you are selling your home you will want to get the best price possible for the sale. There are various property websites around that can help you establish what your home might be worth but why not take a look on&nbsp;<a href="http://www.zoopla.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.zoopla.co.uk</a>&nbsp;and see what other houses in your area are selling for?</p>\r\n<p>Our highly trained conveyancing solicitors in Sheffield and Chesterfield offer support and care to all of our clients. We also offer a professional approach to each case whilst also ensuring that all of our services are fully confidential. Our conveyancing solicitor will provide you with expert advice on selling your house and the processes involved.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Conveyancing solicitors, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:32:29', '2015-07-22 11:05:46', 'At Banner Jones we can give you advice and aid you through the process of selling your house to ensure a smooth and efficient transaction. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>A quality service guaranteed</p>\r\n<p>Call us today for a quote</p>', '182_Accredited CQ_logo rgb.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 61971, '2013-03-28 15:19:55', 'Conveyancing solicitors Chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Selling.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 70932, '2010-12-22 10:13:57', 'Selling', '', '', 'Selling', '/web/contact_us', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a onclick="_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'', ''Guide'', ''Download'', ''Selling your house'']);" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/53_Selling a home process.pdf?1390499695" target="_blank">Selling a House Process Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/53_Selling a home process.pdf?1390499695" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/353_Selling Houes Icon.JPG?1409050907" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a onclick="_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'', ''Guide'', ''Download'', ''Buying and Selling Houses'']);" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/62_Residential Conveyancing - Buying and Selling Houses - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883544" target="_blank">Buying &amp; Selling Houses</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/62_Residential Conveyancing - Buying and Selling Houses - Updated 07.04.14.pdf?1396883544" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/343_Buying &amp; Selling Houses Icon.JPG?1409048697" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Selling a House', ''),
(238, 'Equity Release', 'equity_release', 'Equity Release | Conveyancing Solicitors in Sheffield | Banner Jones ', 130, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>If you''re looking to release some equity from your home Banner Jones can offer helpful advice&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>What is Equity Release?</h2>\r\n<p>There are various equity release schemes which will allow you to release some of the value also known as the equity that is locked in your home. They allow you to obtain either a lump sum or a regular income or both without you having to move home. You will need expert legal and financial advice, if you are considering this option.</p>\r\n<p>Equity Release schemes have earned a poor reputation in former years, but the regime is now much more regulated than it was. We would still strongly advise you to seek proper legal and financial advice before considering it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To find out whether equity release is really for you, we have developed the following article outlining key information:</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../www.bannerjones.co.uk/assets/stored_documents/original/68_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You.pdf?1400502443" target="_blank"></a><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Is Equity Release Right for You'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/68_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You.pdf?1400502443" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/238/contained_images/045e104cd9d4_275_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You 2.png?1400503093" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Is Equity Release Right for You'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/68_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You.pdf?1400502443" target="_blank">Open Article</a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">How does Equity Release work?</span></p>\r\n<p>To be eligible for any of the equity release schemes available, you must generally speaking:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be aged at least 60, own your own home, have paid off all or almost all of any existing mortgage over the property.</li>\r\n<li>Own a property worth at least &pound;40,000.</li>\r\n<li>Own a property built out of brick or stone.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What different Equity Release Schemes are available?</h2>\r\n<p>The schemes fall under 2 broad headings: &ldquo;Reversion Schemes&rdquo; and &ldquo;Lifetime Mortgage Schemes&rdquo;. Each type will have advantages and disadvantages.</p>\r\n<h2>Reversion Scheme</h2>\r\n<p>These <strong>equity release</strong> schemes involve you selling all or part of your home to a Reversion Company. In return, you receive a lump sum or a monthly income. You and your partner can stay in the home, usually rent free, for the rest of your lives. When the property is eventually sold (usually on the 2nd death), the Reversion Company receives a % of the sale proceeds equal to the % of the property that they bought from you.</p>\r\n<h2>Lifetime Mortgage Equity Release Schemes</h2>\r\n<p>This heading covers a variety of different <strong>equity release</strong> mortgage schemes, all of which involve you borrowing money secured on the value of your home. Again, you can receive either a lump sum or a monthly income. You continue to own all of your home and the loan is repaid to the lender when your home is sold. You can choose whether to make interest payments or whether the interest is &ldquo;rolled up&rdquo; and paid back when the property is sold.</p>\r\n<h2>Equity Release costs?</h2>\r\n<p><strong>There are all sorts of &ldquo;hidden&rdquo; costs including:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Completion</li>\r\n<li>Arrangement or application fees</li>\r\n<li>Valuation fees</li>\r\n<li>Insurance</li>\r\n<li>Early repayment charges</li>\r\n<li>Legal fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>You should also consider the following:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If your circumstances change in the future, will you be able to move home? Any <strong>equity release scheme</strong> will affect the inheritance you are able to leave to your children or grandchildren</li>\r\n<li>There could be implications for your entitlement to social security benefits</li>\r\n<li>Who will be responsible for repairs and maintenance of the property?</li>\r\n<li>Tax implications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Is Equity Release right for me?</h2>\r\n<p>It may be that you could consider other options as opposed to <strong>equity release</strong>, such as moving to a smaller property or cashing in other &ldquo;nest eggs&rdquo;, such as premium bonds or savings.</p>\r\n<h2>Equity Release advice</h2>\r\n<p>If you are considering releasing some of the equity in your home, please book an appointment and we will be happy to discuss your options. We can meet you with your financial adviser if you wish, to make sure the advice is integrated. If you do not already have a financial adviser, we would be happy to recommend a specialist, independent adviser who can discuss your circumstances in detail.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Conveyancing solicitors, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2011-03-23 15:56:42', '2015-07-22 11:08:52', 'At Banner Jones we offer helpful advice from our expert conveyancing solicitors on equity release and the process.', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Call today for a quote</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'EquityRelease.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 38659, '2011-03-29 11:59:11', 'Equity Release', '', '', 'Equity Release', '/web/contact_us', '', 9, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/68_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You.pdf?1400502443" target="_blank">Download Equity Release Document</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/68_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You.pdf?1400502443" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/276_Residential Conveyancing - Equity Release - Is Equity Release Right For You graphic.png?1400503138" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Equity Release ', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Conveyancing Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>\r\n'),
(239, 'Funding', 'funding', 'Family Law Funding Solicitors in Sheffield | Legal Aid and Public Funding | Banner Jones', 174, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Banner Jones offer expert advice on the different Funding available to you</h2>\r\n<p>There have been significant changes made to the way in which family and matrimonial legal fees can be met introduced by the government from the 1st of April 2013.</p>\r\n<p>For the vast majority of cases, Public Funding or Legal Aid as we know it has now come to an end. Banner Jones&rsquo; expert family law solicitors in Sheffield can provide expert guidance and advice on if you still qualify for Legal Aid.</p>\r\n<p>As this can be a very complicated process with lots of options available to you, we have prepared a guide for the options for funding your divorce which includes: your own resource options, third party source options, maintenance, insurance, litigation loans, public funding and information on our free Assessment Information Meeting:</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/80_Family Law - Funding Your Divorce.pdf?1403267833" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/239/contained_images/ac08f292bed7_331_Funding your divorce.JPG?1403275929" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Funding Your Divorce'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/80_Family Law - Funding Your Divorce.pdf?1403267833" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<h2>Private Funding</h2>\r\n<p>If you are not eligible for any LSC funding there are various ways in which we can help you fund your case. At Banner Jones we offer fixed fee packages for divorce which helps you to budget in advance. Click here for more information on <a href="../../../page/fixed-fee-divorce" target="_blank">Fixed Fees</a>&nbsp;for divorce. We will also where possible try to offer you a tailor made fixed fee solution for the various stages of your case.</p>\r\n<h2>Legal Aid advice and assistance</h2>\r\n<p>Legal Aid is still available for certain types of family matters. For full information on Legal Aid visit our <a href="../../../page/legal-aid" target="_blank">Legal Aid Page</a> which explains the updated Legal Aid Family Law and will inform you if you could qualify for legal aid assistance.</p>\r\n<h2>Banner Jones Family Assist Scheme</h2>\r\n<p>We recognise the fact that, for a large number of our clients, the sweeping changes to the eligibility for Legal Aid will make things very difficult.&nbsp; We therefore have introduced a scheme to help people who are on a low income, who would normally have come within the scope of Legal Aid but, because of the new requirements, no longer do so.&nbsp; Our scheme is called <a href="../../../page/family-assist-scheme" target="_blank">Family Assist.</a></p>\r\n<h2>Family Mediation</h2>\r\n<p>Funding may be available for the mediation&nbsp;of a family dispute. This means trying to reach an agreed settlement with the help of an independent mediator. See our&nbsp;<a href="../../../page/mediation" target="_blank"><strong>M</strong><strong>ediation</strong></a><strong>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;section for further details.</p>\r\n<h2>Banner Jones expert Family Solicitors</h2>\r\n<p>Our expert family law solicitors are highly experienced and will treat each case uniquely depending on your circumstances. Our family law specialists achieve solutions through confidential settlements and are always on hand to provide support when resolving family law issues.</p>\r\n<p>We have&nbsp;offices in Chesterfield, Sheffield, Dronfield, Mansfield, Nottingham, Derby, Ilkeston and Bulwell.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information on funding or legal aid, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Family Law department, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2012-02-23 11:37:30', '2015-07-22 09:33:41', 'Specialist family law solicitors offer expert advice on legal aid and public funding for family law cases. Find out what''s available for you.', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>Fixed Fee Divorce</p>\r\n<p>Click here for more details</p>', '159_man head on bar.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 391589, '2013-04-22 14:57:19', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/80_Family Law - Funding Your Divorce.pdf?1403267833" target="_blank">Download Funding Your Divorce Options Guide</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/80_Family Law - Funding Your Divorce.pdf?1403267833" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/332_Funding your divorce icon.JPG?1403276016" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Family Law Funding ', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Family Law Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>'),
(240, 'Family Assist Scheme', 'family_assist_scheme', 'Family Assist Scheme | Legal Aid & Family Law', 181, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Banner Jones Family Assist Scheme helps bridge the funding gap left by Legal Aid</h2>\r\n<p>The Family Assist Scheme is designed to bridge the funding gap left by the changes to Legal Aid.&nbsp; It is based on the previous Legal Aid criteria and will be used to identify those whose income and capital resources are limited and who may benefit from a scheme assisted reduction in their family law fees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Eligibility for Family Assist Scheme</h2>\r\n<p><strong>The eligibility test consists of&nbsp;three stages:</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Capital Assessment</p>\r\n<p>2. Income Assessment</p>\r\n<p>3. Affordability Test</p>\r\n<p>The capital and income eligibility is broadly in line with the funding limits set prior to 1 April 2013.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The affordability test takes into consideration debts and other outgoings that you are committed to which may affect your ability to pay for the services that you require.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If it was felt that, looking at your overall financial circumstances, you were able to contribute towards the legal fees that you are likely to incur then, on the basis that you set up a standing order at an agreed rate and sign a Notice of Acting in Person, which we can hold on the file for us to use should we require it, then we will sign you up to Family Assist, as long as you are within the relevant capital and income criteria.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If we sign you up to Family Assist, then we will charge &pound;99 per hour plus VAT.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Reduced Charging Rate Family Assist Scheme</h2>\r\n<p>If it was felt that, due to debts and other outgoings, you would not be able to contribute towards your legal fees but that you had somebody else who was willing to pay those fees for you, such as relative, partner or friend, then you may benefit from the scheme and the reduced charging rate provided there is a suitable signed guarantee form from the payer, together with a standing order mandate form at an agreed rate and a Notice of Acting in Person.</p>\r\n<p>Once these are in place, the Family Assist reduced charging rate would apply to your matter.</p>\r\n<p>Please note that, should the standing order mandate form be stopped or unpaid by the bank, the reduced rate will cease and Banner Jones will be entitled, with immediate effect, to cease all further work until such time as the payments are re-started, to lodge the Notice of Acting in Person form with the Court and to apply the fee earner&rsquo;s normal charging rate to any work already carried out and to include these increased fees in any final account.</p>\r\n<p>We have&nbsp;offices in Chesterfield, Sheffield, Dronfield, Mansfield, Nottingham, Derby, Ilkeston and Bulwell.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information about the Family Assist Scheme, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Family Law department, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2013-04-22 13:47:55', '2015-06-10 10:42:31', 'Our specialist family law solicitors offer expert advice to individuals who may qualify for a family assist scheme. Find out what''s available for you.', '', 5, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, 'Giving you a helping hand', 'family_assist_logo_FINAL_WHITE.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 61259, '2013-04-22 14:40:48', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '', '', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Family Law Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>'),
(241, 'Legal Aid', 'legal_aid', 'Legal Aid Solicitors | Legal Aid Family Law | Banner Jones', 182, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Banner Jones provide the latest up to date Legal Aid advice</h2>\r\n<h2><strong>You can still qualify for Legal Aid support in some cases:</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If your case is in relation to children, where the Local Authority Social Services are taking Care Proceedings in relation to those children, then funding is still available</li>\r\n<li>Domestic Violence Injunction Cases, where you need protection from somebody who is being violent or abusive towards you</li>\r\n<li>Cases relating to Divorce, financial matters and children, where there is evidence of domestic violence</li>\r\n<li>Cases in relation to Residence and Contact of children, where there is evidence of child abuse</li>\r\n<li>Child Abduction</li>\r\n<li>Representation for a child in Private Family Cases</li>\r\n<li>Legal advice in support of mediation (no evidence of domestic violence is needed)</li>\r\n<li>Forced Marriage Protection Order Cases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Is there any other circumstances where I can qualify for Legal Aid?</h2>\r\n<p>For most people, where there is no domestic violence within the relationship, or domestic violence that can be proved to the standard required by the Legal Aid Authority, there is no Public Funding available for Divorce, Dissolution of Civil Partnerships, financial matters and children matters.</p>\r\n<h2>What counts as Domestic Violence?</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The Legal Aid Authority will accept the following evidence as domestic violence outlined in our PDF article below: &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Family law What Counts as Domestic Violence'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/65_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as domestic violence.pdf?1400498116" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/241/contained_images/e65ccbdb7ea9_398_What counts as domestic violence.jpg?1421859490" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Family law What Counts as Domestic Violence'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/65_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as domestic violence.pdf?1400498116" target="_blank">Open Article</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">This must be provided by you before we are able to sign you up to any form of Legal Aid, unless you are looking for Help with Mediation, a Domestic Violence Injunction or Local Authority Care Proceedings relating to children.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Please note that the allegations have to be in relation to the person that you are currently having problems with.&nbsp; These allegations cannot be in relation to a previous or different partner as you will not qualify for Legal Aid.</p>\r\n<h2>What counts as Evidence that Children are at Risk?</h2>\r\n<p>The Legal Aid Authority will accept the following evidence of children being at risk of abuse outlined in our PDF article below:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/64_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as evidence that children are at risk.pdf?1400498096" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/241/contained_images/f92cc79c0fef_397_Children_at_risk.JPG?1421859334" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Family law Evidence that Children are at Risk'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/64_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as evidence that children are at risk.pdf?1400498096" target="_blank">Open Article</a></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Fees for providing evidence to support your case</strong></h2>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones we cannot pay for any of the above evidence to be provided.&nbsp; If there is a charge for producing the evidence, we cannot pay it: you will need to meet these costs yourself and then bring the evidence to us.</p>\r\n<p>Even in urgent cases, we cannot exercise our Delegated Functions and give you an emergency Legal Aid Certificate without the evidence of domestic violence or child abuse as set out above.&nbsp;There are standard letters that have been approved by the Ministry of Justice.&nbsp; For more information about this generally and to access those standard letters, <a href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/legal-aid-for-private-family-matters/legal-aid-divorcing-separating-abusive-partner" target="_blank">click here.&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;">Help with Family Mediation</span></p>\r\n<p>There is a new level of Legal Aid available to help give advice to people who are going through the mediation process.&nbsp; This is called Help with Family Mediation.&nbsp; This allows us to provide you with the legal advice whilst you are going through mediation or immediately following a mediation process.&nbsp; You will still need to meet the normal means and merits test, but we will be able to work through this with you.&nbsp; You will need to bring with you the relevant form from your Mediation Service to show that you are currently going through mediation or have been in mediation within the last 3 months.</p>\r\n<p>We have&nbsp;offices in Chesterfield, Sheffield, Dronfield, Mansfield, Nottingham, Derby, Ilkeston and Bulwell.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information on Legal Aid, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Family Law department, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2013-04-22 14:18:41', '2015-06-10 10:42:50', 'Our specialist family law solicitors offer expert advice on legal aid and if you could qualify. Find out what support is available to you.', '', 5, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>If you are not eliglible for Legal Aid our New Family Assist Scheme offers you a service at significantly discounted fees.</p>\r\n<p>Giving you a helping hand</p>', 'family_assist_logo_FINAL_WHITE.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 61259, '2013-04-22 14:55:28', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/page/family-assist-scheme', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/family-assist-scheme', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/65_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as domestic violence.pdf?1400498116" target="_blank">Download Domestic Violence Article</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/65_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as domestic violence.pdf?1400498116" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/268_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as domestic violence graphic.png?1400498679" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/64_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as evidence that children are at risk.pdf?1400498096" target="_blank">Download Children at Risk Article</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/64_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as evidence that children are at risk.pdf?1400498096" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/269_Family Law - Legal Aid - What counts as evidence that children are at risk graphic.png?1400498851" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Legal Aid Solicitors', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Family Law Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>'),
(242, 'Divorce and Separation', 'divorce_and_seperation', 'Divorce Solicitors in Sheffield & Chesterfield | Banner Jones', 49, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2 style="text-align: left;">Banner Jones provide expert Divorce advice and guidance</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">You are probably worrying about where you are going to live, whether you&rsquo;ll keep your children and how much money you will have. Don&rsquo;t worry; Banner Jones expert divorce solicitors are here to help you with the legal issues, and provide you with expert divorce advice. Whether you are married, or have been living with your partner, our experienced team of family law solicitors will advise you on resolving divorce issues, and help you get the best outcome to suit your needs.</p>\r\n<p>Are you local to Sheffield and are going through a tough time during a divorce or separation? Our family law solicitors have created a guide of things to do in Sheffield to keep you busy and get you back on your feet during this time.</p>\r\n<p><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Sheffield Divorce Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/125_BannerJonesDivorceGuideV2.pdf?1435138228" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/242/contained_images/6df1b70d95d5_442_Banner Jones divorce logo.jpg?1435138044" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Sheffield Divorce Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/125_BannerJonesDivorceGuideV2.pdf?1435138228" target="_blank">Open Guide</a></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">How to get a Divorce without attending Court</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Many of our clients worry about going to court when they come to see us, but be assured there are several divorce options available that will avoid you going to court. Collaborative family law is one of the modern approaches to divorce and has been labelled as a good divorce as you can agree from the outset that you will not go to court. We do appreciate however, that not all divorce cases are the same and if going to Court is your chosen route then we''ll be with you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Why Choose Banner Jones as your Divorce Solicitors?</h2>\r\n<ul style="text-align: left;">\r\n<li>We have one of the largest Family Law teams in NE Derbyshire and Sheffield</li>\r\n<li>You have a choice of&nbsp;5 offices across Chesterfield, Dronfield Sheffield and Mansfield</li>\r\n<li>We have a mixed team of male and female divorce solicitors so if you have a preference then you can choose who you see</li>\r\n<li>We are experienced in high value matrimonial cases</li>\r\n<li>We are Resolution accredited</li>\r\n<li>We have Collaborative lawyers in our team</li>\r\n<li>We have Children law specialists in our team</li>\r\n<li>We have an independent mediation service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAt Banner Jones we want to help ease your mind and walk you through the process, because we know how stressful divorce can be. Why not take a look at our free guides below? The first offers some advice regarding divorce and separation and the second will help you get to know the divorce process in detail.\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/66_Family Law - Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet.pdf?1400499976" target="_blank"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/242/contained_images/8b274c759f0e_308_Divorce 2.JPG?1402590534" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></h2>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Family law A Guide To Divorce and Separation'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/66_Family Law - Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet.pdf?1400499976" target="_blank">Open Article</a></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/67_Banner Jones Divorce Infographic V5 FINAL.pdf?1400500109" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/242/contained_images/22aba97ba4f4_272_Family Law - Divorce infographic.png?1400500537" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></h2>\r\n<p class="standout_link" style="text-align: center;"><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Family law divorce The Banner Jones process'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/67_Banner Jones Divorce Infographic V5 FINAL.pdf?1400500109" target="_blank">&nbsp;Open Infographic</a></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Experienced Divorce Solicitors</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If your financial&nbsp;circumstances&nbsp;are complex and you need advice on the division of high value matrimonial assets and property, then we have the experience to help you reach the best solution.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Some couples are able to resolve their situation amicably through Family&nbsp;<a href="../../../page/mediation" target="_blank">Mediation</a>. To read more about our family mediation services visit our mediation page.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Our expert divorce solicitors are highly experienced and will treat each case uniquely depending on your circumstances. Our family law specialists achieve solutions through confidential settlements and are always on hand to provide support as we know going through a divorce can be a stressful time. We have worked on many family law divorce cases and we ensure each of our clients receive the utmost care and consideration throughout the case.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">We have&nbsp;offices in Chesterfield, Sheffield, Dronfield, Mansfield, Nottingham, Derby, Ilkeston and Bulwell.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>For more information, or to arrange an appointment with our expert Family Law department, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2010-11-15 10:34:24', '2015-08-06 13:01:52', 'Our specialist divorce solicitors offer expert advice and guidance on divorce & family law through this stressful time. ', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p><strong>Affordable&nbsp;Fixed Fee Divorce</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Giving you the choice...</strong></p>', '83_iStock_000007854419XSmall.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 99712, '2013-02-19 10:01:02', 'Divorce solicitor chesterfield', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'DivorceAndSeparation.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 56028, '2011-01-13 16:16:24', 'Divorce and Separation', '', '', 'Divorce and Separation', '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', 10, 'family_highlight', '', '/page/fixed-fee-divorce', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Step by Step Guide'', ''Open'', ''Relationship Breakdown Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/156_BJ_RELATIONSHIP_6PP_SINGLE.pdf?1438859570" target="_blank">Download our Step by Step Guide to Relationship Breakdown</a></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Step by Step Guide'', ''Open'', ''Relationship Breakdown Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/156_BJ_RELATIONSHIP_6PP_SINGLE.pdf?1438859570" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/460_Banner-Jones-Divorce-Cover.JPG?1438859531" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/67_Banner Jones Divorce Infographic V5 FINAL.pdf?1400500109" target="_blank">Download Divorce and Separation Infographic</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/66_Family Law - Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet.pdf?1400499976" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/304_Divorce &amp; Separation article icon.JPG?1402502195" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/66_Family Law - Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet.pdf?1400499976" target="_blank">Download Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/66_Family Law - Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet.pdf?1400499976" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/271_Family Law - Divorce and Separation Fact Sheet graphic.png?1400499926" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>', 'Specialist Divorce Solicitors', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Family Law Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>'),
(243, 'Fixed Fee Divorce', 'fixed_fee_divorce', 'Fixed Fee Divorce in Sheffield & Chesterfield | Banner Jones ', 124, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2>Banner Jones Fixed Fee Divorce Solicitors</h2>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones we know that everyone&rsquo;s circumstances are different and that some clients may require more support during the divorce process than others. By our expert divorce solicitors working with our clients and understanding their needs we&rsquo;ve been able to develop two fixed fee divorce packages, which gives you the choice of how you want your divorce to be managed.</p>\r\n<p>We can offer our fixed fee divorce packages in all of our offices across Chesterfield and Sheffield giving you even more flexibility. We have expert divorce solicitors located at each of our offices who can guide you through the fixed fee divorce process.</p>\r\n<h2>Different Types of Fixed Fee Divorce Packages</h2>\r\n<h2><strong>1. Forms Assist Fixed Fee Package: &pound;300&nbsp;</strong>(<strong>+VAT &amp; Court Fees)</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Forms Assist gives you the&nbsp;flexibility and control to&nbsp;manage the divorce process yourself, but with the added reassurance that all of the forms you need will be provided fully completed and ready for you to simply lodge with the Court.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We will send you all of the forms by e-mail or post (whichever you prefer), together with a comprehensive guide on how to progress the proceedings. Be reassured however that we''ll offer expert advice and support through the fixed fee divorce process as you will be given a contact for e-mail and phone support.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What&rsquo;s included in the fixed feed divorce package?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>No meeting required, details taken over the phone</li>\r\n<li>All the forms you need for Court, fully completed and checked by us</li>\r\n<li>A comprehensive guide as to how to lodge the forms with the Court</li>\r\n<li>A contact number/e-mail for a specialist divorce solicitor who can advise you at any stage along the way</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>2. Complete Assist Fixed Fee Package: &pound;500 (+VAT and Court Fees)</h2>\r\n<p>Complete Assist may be more suitable if your circumstances are slightly more complex and you do not want the inconvenience and responsibility of dealing with the Court yourself. The Complete Assist Fixed Fee Package gives you the reassurance that your dedicated and expert divorce solicitor will file all of the forms on your behalf and deal with any correspondence from the Court, whilst keeping you up to date with progress along the way.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What&rsquo;s included in the fixed fee divorce package?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Face to Face meeting with your family law solicitor to discuss the case</li>\r\n<li>All forms fully completed and lodged with the Court on your behalf</li>\r\n<li>Regular contact from your divorce solicitor who will update you on the progress of the case</li>\r\n<li>All Court correspondence dealt with on your behalf</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Contact a Solicitor today for more information on our Fixed Fee Divorce packages &nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Our expert divorce solicitors are highly experienced and will treat each case uniquely depending on your circumstances. Our family law specialists achieve solutions through confidential settlements and we can help you make informed decisions on where a fixed feed divorce is right for you. We have worked on many fixed fee divorces and we ensure each of our clients receive the upmost care and consideration throughout the divorce process.</p>\r\n<p>We have&nbsp;offices in Chesterfield, Sheffield, Dronfield, Mansfield, Nottingham, Derby, Ilkeston and Bulwell.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you are considering a fixed fee divorce, need divorce advice, or would like to arrange an appointment with our expert Family Law department, call <span class="calltracks_bannerjonescouk-main">0330 017 6309</span></strong>*<strong>&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@bannerjones.co.uk">info@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>*<strong><sub>calls cost no more than a local 01 number and are included in your mobile minutes.</sub></strong></p>', '2011-02-25 14:45:39', '2015-08-06 11:25:02', 'We offer fixed fee divorce packages as we know everyone’s case is different, therefore giving you more flexibility. See which suits you.', '', 5, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0, '<p>If your family circumstances are changing you&nbsp;should update your Will</p>\r\n<p>Contact us now</p>', '49_wom with baby.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 185944, '2011-05-19 15:21:34', '', 'family_highlight', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, 'family_highlight', '', '/web/contact_us', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 0, '<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Step by Step Guide'', ''Open'', ''Relationship Breakdown Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/156_BJ_RELATIONSHIP_6PP_SINGLE.pdf?1438859570" target="_blank">Download our Step by Step Guide to Relationship Breakdown</a></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Step by Step Guide'', ''Open'', ''Relationship Breakdown Guide'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/156_BJ_RELATIONSHIP_6PP_SINGLE.pdf?1438859570" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/460_Banner-Jones-Divorce-Cover.JPG?1438859531" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a onclick="pageTracker._trackEvent(''Infographic'', ''Open'', ''Family law divorce The Banner Jones process'');" href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/63_Banner Jones Divorce Infographic V4.pdf?1397223871" target="_blank">Download Divorce and Separation Infographic</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/67_Banner Jones Divorce Infographic V5 FINAL.pdf?1400500109" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/stored_images/original/272_Family Law - Divorce infographic.png?1400500537" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Fixed Fee Divorce', '<div itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Review-aggregate">\r\n    <span itemprop="itemreviewed">Banner Jones Family Law Reviews</span>    \r\n    <span itemprop="rating" itemscope itemtype="http://data-vocabulary.org/Rating">\r\n      <span itemprop="average">4.5</span>\r\n      out of <span itemprop="best">5</span>\r\n    </span>\r\n    based on <span itemprop="votes">6</span> ratings.    \r\n</div>');
