(8, 'Anne Rogers', 'Solicitor ', 'AnneRogers@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 560', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-03 12:29:32', '2015-03-09 16:39:36', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 33, '183_ar large 2012.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 117044, '2013-04-11 13:21:46', 'Anne Rogers Wills and Probate Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Studied at De Montfort University, Leicester', '2009', 'Anne originally worked for Glossops before the firm merged with Banner Jones Middleton in June 2007. \r\n', '', '', 'Dancing Teacher', 'Walking, Yoga, Eating Out', 'A nice glass of white wine!', 'Two weeks in the Maldives', '120 mile walk - Cleveland Way', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 'Since qualifying in 2009 Anne has concentrated on Private Client work and has developed a particular interest and expertise in matters relating to the elderly client. Anne specialises in the areas of&nbsp;<a href="../../../page/wills" target="_blank">Wills</a>, <a href="../../../page/probate" target="_blank">Probate,</a> Enduring and Lasting Powers of Attorney and Court of Protection work.<br />', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(9, 'Michael Parker', 'Litigation Executive', 'MichaelParker@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560565', 'Glumangate ', '2011-02-07 11:23:34', '2015-02-05 12:15:10', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 44, 'MichaelParker.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 98571, '2011-03-03 14:58:39', 'Michael Parker Dispute Resolution', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', 'Michael applies over 15 years of experience in Debt matters and General Litigation as he works on a wide range of matters for both Claimants and Defendants in all areas of Dispute Resolution and Civil Litigation.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Michael&rsquo;s principal specialisms are acting in relation to both commercial and residential property disputes, and in particular helping Landlords of residential tenancies with possession proceedings.</p>\r\n<p>Michael likes to take a considered approach to all disputes by clearly establishing the client&rsquo;s concerns and intentions and he always looks to find to the most cost effective resolution.</p>\r\n<p>Michael&rsquo;s main areas of work include:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Debt      Recovery</li>\r\n<li>Possession      Proceedings - Residential and Commercial</li>\r\n<li>General      Landlord and Tenant &ndash; Residential and Commercial</li>\r\n<li>Contractual      disputes</li>\r\n<li>Neighbour      and boundary disputes</li>\r\n<li>General      commercial and civil disputes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Michael joined Banner Jones in March 2008 as a Litigation Executive in the Dispute Resolution Department,&nbsp;having previously worked in the legal departments of Close Brothers and the RAC.</p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(16, 'Jayne Henshaw', 'Compliance Officer for Legal Practice', 'JayneHenshaw@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560543', '26 Glumangate', '2011-02-07 11:35:22', '2015-03-09 16:57:03', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 5, 'Jayne Henshaw.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 193591, '2014-10-15 10:32:22', 'Jayne Henshaw', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'University of Huddersfield', '1988', 'Jayne is a practising Solicitor, Director of Banner Jones and currently holds the role of the company’s Compliance Officer for Legal Practice and Money Laundering Reporting Officer. ', '', 'Jayne is a member of the Derby Law Society and a member of the Law Society Risk and Compliance Service', 'Putting bottoms in Smarties tubes in a factory', 'Trying to train a Labrador, and Karate', 'Gin', 'Russia', 'Learning to speak Serbo Croat', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Jayne has played a leading role in developing best practice and risk management at Banner Jones. She utilises her wealth of experience and knowledge to the benefit of our clients by:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>overseeing our client care policies and risk management;</li>\r\n<li>ensuring compliance with our statutory obligations and those set by our regulatory body, the Solicitors Regulation Authority, including anti-money laundering and anti-terrorism; </li>\r\n<li>auditing the work of members of our various teams to ensure high standards of service are delivered. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Compliance is sometimes seen as a &lsquo;tick box&rsquo; exercise but at Banner Jones we make those systems part of our culture; they are part of the service you receive as one of our clients whether you are an individual or a business. It is also how we ensure quality and consistency of client service and how we manage the risks to our clients that legal work inevitably generates. We do this by training our staff and we ensure that compliance is at the core of what we do. We constantly review how we work so that we can deal with new situations in a pro-active way and so that our systems are always up to date.</p>\r\n<p>Accreditations: As testament to our systems in April 2012 we secured a renewal of the Specialist Quality Mark for our legally aided work in our Crime, Family and Family Mediation Departments. We also obtained the Law Society&rsquo;s accreditation to be part of their Conveyancing Quality Scheme (CQS) and have just been approved for a second year.</p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(17, 'Andrew Fielder', 'Solicitor, Director', 'AndrewFielder@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 560', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 11:36:32', '2015-03-18 11:03:57', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 15, 'AndrewFielder.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 100986, '2011-02-07 11:36:31', 'Andrew Fielder Commercial Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'LLB (Hons) University of Nottingham', '2007', 'Andrew joined Banner Jones as a Trainee Solicitor in September 2005, qualifying in September 2007. Andrew undertakes a mixture of corporate and commercial property work including: company formations, commercial agreements, business sales and purchases, shareholder and partnership agreements, commercial leases, development projects and commercial premises sales and acquisitions.\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Building site labourer', 'Football (both playing and supporting), golf and hiking.', 'Milk', 'Round the world trip ', 'Learning to do some DIY following the purchase of my house.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(18, 'Peter Jones', 'Solicitor - Director', 'PeterJones@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 283016 ', 'Marsden Street', '2011-02-07 11:36:57', '2015-03-09 15:59:47', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 2, 'PeterJones.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 97616, '2011-02-07 11:36:56', 'Peter Jones Family Law Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'University of Kent', '', 'When you contact me it will be because you are dealing with significant changes in your life and need help.  I apply detailed knowledge of the law and over 30 years of experience to support you through change.  For nearly 15 years I was the Banner Jones partner responsible for the Staveley office, which gave me a breadth of experience in legal problems.\r\n', 'Re: S (2012)\r\n\r\nI represented grandparents whose daughter’s baby was going to be taken into care.  I successfully argued that she should be cared for by my clients, and the case ended with a Special Guardianship Order being made in their favour\r\n\r\n', 'Member of the Criminal Litigation panel', 'Washing up in a restaurant on the south coast of France in 100 degree heat.  Worst job in the world. ', 'I sing in the Chesterfield Philharmonic Choir, of which I am the chairman.  I enjoy going out with friends and going to music festivals with my grown up children and their friends and their fathers', 'A light sharp hoppy bitter', 'In the garden of our house in Brittany, chopping up wood, pulling up weeds, cutting the lawn. I am very fortunate that I get the chance to do that often.', 'Arriving in time for Bestival at the Isle of Wight, and wearing a ridiculous costume throughout.', '138_crim lit.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 57584, '2011-11-09 16:34:03', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p style="text-align: left;">My clients include parents and other relatives trying to make arrangements for <a href="../../../page/contact" target="_blank">contact with children</a>, couples separating and needing me to deal with their finances, victims (both men and women) of domestic violence, parents and grandparents where social services have become involved with children.&nbsp; I have for many years been a member of the Child Care Panel.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">I am a Duty Solicitor and give urgent personal support to clients arrested or before the Magistrates.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">I focus on the issues that matter and advise you what your options are.&nbsp; I believe in giving frank, straightforward and clear advice.&nbsp; I ensure you know how the law applies to your case.&nbsp; I support you to make the right choices, and put them into effect.&nbsp; I am a member of Resolution and subscribe to their Code of Practice that can be found here: <a href="http://www.resolution.org.uk/">http://www.resolution.org.uk</a>.&nbsp; Resolution commits family lawyers to resolving disputes in a non-confrontational way wherever possible.&nbsp; I share the belief that family law disputes should be dealt with in a constructive way designed to preserve people&rsquo;s dignity and to encourage agreement.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><br />Family problems are most often based on in a lack of communication.&nbsp; Negotiation, even at the door of the court, is very important in all areas of law but particularly family law.&nbsp; There is not a week goes by when I am not at court personally advising my clients, representing their interests, and presenting their case.</p>', '<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Re:&nbsp; M (2012)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I ensured my client on divorce, had the matrimonial home transferred into her name, so that she retains the full value of the asset she brought into the marriage.<br />&nbsp;<br /><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Re:&nbsp; W (2012)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My client was victim of significant abuse and violence from her former partner.&nbsp; He denied everything.&nbsp; After a full day&rsquo;s court hearing the Judge agreed that all 18 of the allegations against him, including the most serious, were proven.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; C (2012)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My client&rsquo;s baby was taken into foster care after birth.&nbsp; Mother had a recent history of drug abuse and domestic violence.&nbsp; I supported mother in her decision that the best interests of her daughter was adoption to a safe and secure family home as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Re:&nbsp; S (2012)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My client was a victim of domestic abuse and intimidation and manipulation by her former partner the father of her child.&nbsp; I supported her and helped her to understand how she was being abused.&nbsp; I directed her to the agencies that could provide her with help.&nbsp; She grew in confidence and eventually with my help was able to make a complaint to the police.&nbsp; Her former partner is now charged with harassment and subject to a restraining order.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Re:&nbsp; M (2011)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My client wanted contact with a child he had never met.&nbsp; However he continued to be in trouble with the police.&nbsp; I advised him what steps he needed to take before he could apply to the court for a contact order.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; C (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Social Services alleged that my client&rsquo;s toddler was at risk of harm from him and his partner and applied to take the child into care.&nbsp; I successfully defended an application to remove the child and at the final hearing I argued my client&rsquo;s case and the Magistrates rejected the social services&rsquo; concerns.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; C (2012)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Social Services alleged my client was by not able to protect his small boy.&nbsp; At an interim hearing the Judge ordered that his son should be removed from his care but I arranged for assessments which resulted in him being returned to his father&rsquo;s care and the family reunited.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re: C (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I acted for grandmother.&nbsp; The her two grand-children lived with her.&nbsp; Mother wanted them returned to her.&nbsp; Over a long court case we answered objection after objection raised by mother to grandmother&rsquo;s care of the children but eventually at a final hearing the arrangements were confirmed and an order made that the children should continue to live with their grandmother, my client.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; T (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My clients received threatening letters from a solicitor instructed by grandmother demanding contact with their children.&nbsp; I advised an approach which contained an offer of contact and a robust set of expectations from grandmother.&nbsp; The grandmother solicitors&rsquo; letters were shown to be empty threats.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp;&nbsp; V (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Acting for mother in divorce proceedings I helped negotiate a mutually satisfactory agreement for the shared care of the children.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Re:&nbsp;&nbsp; H (2011)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I acted for father who was accused of domestic violence towards his wife.&nbsp; At the end of lengthy court proceedings Social Services accepted that mother had an alcohol problem which made the disharmony worse, and the children were placed in the primary care of their father.&nbsp; We negotiated contact with mother, and also put in place a negotiated financial arrangement.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re: F (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Father and mother could not agree how to share the care of their young children.&nbsp; On my advice mother had put forward a proposal for shared care that she considered to be in the best interests of the children.&nbsp; Father alleged that the children were not safe in their mother&rsquo;s care.&nbsp; After a 3 day hearing the judge accepted my client&rsquo;s case and rejected all father&rsquo;s allegations.&nbsp; The judge made an order in the terms of the proposal we had made.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; L (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Divorce proceedings were relatively straightforward but, although we made a number of offers, husband would not come to agreement on the financial matters.&nbsp; At a final hearing, with evidence being given by both husband and wife, I established that husband had assets abroad that he had not properly disclosed and the full value of the matrimonial home was transferred to my client the wife.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; E (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My client was the mother of a delightful little boy but her lifestyle caused social services to intervene claiming that she was unable to give him the care and attention that he needed.&nbsp; I advised my client, and who agreed that her son lived with her parents, so she is able to continue to maintain a relationship with him and the threat of adoption was removed.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re:&nbsp; S (2011)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">My client, the husband, lived in the matrimonial home and although it was in his sole name had always agreed that his former wife was entitled to one half of it.&nbsp; In negotiation with the wife&rsquo;s solicitors an arrangement was reached which allowed him to continue to live in the property and did not affect the benefits entitlement of either husband or wife.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(19, 'Rachel Barlow', 'Chartered Legal Executive', 'RachelBarlow@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 283004', 'Marsden Street', '2011-02-07 11:38:56', '2015-03-16 12:29:51', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 42, 'DSC_9020 Rachael Barlow.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 160961, '2015-03-16 09:51:03', 'Rachael Barlow Family Law ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '2003', 'Rachel recognises that the breakdown of a relationship is often a very stressful time for all concerned and aims to deal with matters in as sensitive a way as possible, maintaining a friendly and down to earth approach.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Checkout operator at Morrisons.', 'Gym, reading, socialising, walking', 'Glass of Pinot Grigio, or a cup of tea.', 'Two weeks in the Maldives doing nothing but sunbathing and snorkelling', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Rachel specialises in advising and assisting clients with regard to all issues arising from the breakdown of their relationship, including <a href="../../../page/divorce-and-separation" target="_blank">divorce</a>, cohabitation disputes, financial disputes, issues concerning children and <a href="../../../page/domestic-violence" target="_blank">domestic abuse</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Rachel has recently been nominated and shortlisted for The National Family Law Awards 2012.&nbsp; The Family Law awards were launched by Jordan Publishing to highlight the important work done by family lawyers and to celebrate their commitment, hard work and outstanding achievements.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(20, 'Richard Barlow', 'Solicitor, Director', 'RichardBarlow@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560530', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 11:39:34', '2015-03-09 16:36:35', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 31, 'Richard Barlow.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 146231, '2014-10-15 10:37:37', 'Richard Barlow ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '2000', 'Richard is a Director and Head of the Private Client Department.  He specialises in:\r\n- Setting up of Wills for clients, tailored to their needs\r\n- The administration of deceased’s estates\r\n- Inheritance tax planning\r\n- The completion and registration of powers of attorney \r\n- Advising the elderly regarding the preservation of their assets\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Paper Round', 'Playing and watching football (but only if it''s Sheffield United), running', 'A pint of Easy Rider real ale', 'Either 3 weeks on a deserted Maldivian island or walking in the Scottish Highlands (in summer)', 'Raising over £1200 for charity by running 51.5 miles in 24 hours', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Richard recognises that for clients these are often very sensitive and difficult matters emotionally to deal with and he&nbsp;aims to ensure that the process involved runs as smoothly and stress-free as possible.</p>\r\n<p>Richard qualified as a solicitor in January 2000 and since then have gained considerable and valuable experience in dealing with Private Client matters, from the more simple and straightforward through to complex and high value estates and tax planning schemes.&nbsp;He has&nbsp;dealt with the estate of a person who died without a Will and who left 99 relatives all of whom he traced and between whom&nbsp;he distributed the estate.</p>\r\n<p>Richard has dealt with multi-million pound value estates upon which&nbsp;he has successfully reduced <a href="../../../page/inheritance-tax" target="_blank">Inheritance Tax </a>to a minimum by applying the appropriate tax reliefs available. He has experience in dealing with all aspects of an estate including the registration of the death, arranging of the funeral and arranging that where appropriate unoccupied property is maintained, insured and secure.</p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(22, 'Sally Cother', 'Property Executive', 'SallyCother@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 414531', 'Dronfield', '2011-02-07 11:40:50', '2015-03-13 15:59:45', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 22, 'DSC_8983 Sally Cother.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 154176, '2015-03-13 15:59:43', 'Sally Cother Conveyancer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', 'Sally came to work for Banner Jones as a Property Executive in our Residential Property team based at our Dronfield office.  Sally is currently working closely with Gleeson developments in Bolsover and Sheffield.', '', '', 'Sales Assistant ', 'Hill Walking/Outdoor pursuits ', 'A good red wine ', '5 Star luxury and hot and sunny', 'This year I walked the 26 mile White Peak Challenge', '167_CQS Logo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 73870, '2012-03-22 12:25:33', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(23, 'Sarah Nadin', 'Solicitor, Director', 'SarahNadin@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 529', 'Mansfield', '2011-02-07 11:41:32', '2015-03-09 14:21:30', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 30, 'sarah n no scarf.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 188479, '2014-03-04 15:46:43', 'Sarah Nadin Wills and Probate Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'University of Warwick LLB (Hons)', '1996', 'Sarah is a Director and Solicitor in the Private Client Department and Family Business Team.  She is also Head of the Private Client Department.  Sarah deals with the administration of a deceased''s estate (probate), the creation and administration of trusts, powers of attorney, application to the Court of Protection (where clients no longer have mental capacity to manage their own affairs), inheritance tax and asset preservation planning and preparation of Wills.', '', 'Sarah is a member of the Society of Trust and Estate Practitioners (STEP).\r\nSarah is also a fully trained corporate member of ICFIB (International Centre for Families in Business)', 'Saturday job on Woolworth''s record counter', 'Lego and pretend tea-parties!', 'Hot Chocolate complete with marshmallows and cream or Wine', 'Ideal = a greek island in the sun or Whistler mountain in the snow.\r\n\r\n \r\nReality = a week in Scarborough making sandcastles on the beach', 'I''m learning to ride and I haven''t fallen off.... yet!', 'STEP_Logosmall.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 13079, '2011-11-10 10:36:38', '', '', '31_ICFIB_LOGO_STRAPnew.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 94666, '2011-11-10 10:36:38', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p><span>Sarah specialises in Compensation Protection Trusts for clients receiving a compensation award following a personal injury or medical negligence.&nbsp; I have specialist knowledge of company commercial matters and as member&nbsp;of the<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="../../../page/family-business" target="_blank"><strong>Family Business Team<span>&nbsp;</span></strong></a>provide succession planning advice as well as company and partnership law advice.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>She qualified as a solicitor in 1996 and undertook further training and exams to gain the Society Trust and Estate Practitioners (STEP) Diploma which she passed with a distinction in December 2008.&nbsp; As a result Sarah is one of only two members of STEP in Chesterfield.&nbsp; Sarah has been involved with all aspects of estate administration including the registration of the death, arranging funerals, rehoming pets, securing and insuring property and dealing with insolvent estates.&nbsp; She regularly travels to see clients at their home where they are unable to attend the office.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Sarah attends and speaks about subjects such as<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="../../../page/wills" target="_blank"><strong>Wills<span>&nbsp;</span></strong></a>and<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="../../../page/lasting-power-of-attorney" target="_blank"><strong>Lasting Powers of Attorney<span>&nbsp;</span></strong></a>at local pensioner''s groups and at seminars and regularly write articles for newspapers and other publications.</span></p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(31, 'Rob Stubbs', 'Solicitor, Director, Head of Dispute Resolution', 'RobStubbs@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 560', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 12:01:33', '2014-09-05 10:53:24', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 35, 'RobStubbs.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 82723, '2011-02-07 12:01:32', 'Rob Stubbs Dispute Resolution Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'LLB, Sheffield Hallam University', '2006', 'Rob qualified as a solicitor in 2006, having studied Law at Sheffield Hallam University and after completing the Legal Practice Course at the University of Sheffield.  He joined Banner Jones in 2004 and became a Director in 2012.  Rob specialises in all aspects of Dispute Resolution, including the following types of case:\r\n\r\n', 'Examples of notable cases dealt with include:\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<ul>\r\n<li>Complex contractual disputes</li>\r\n<li>Commercial disputes</li>\r\n<li>Commercial Property disputes</li>\r\n<li>Residential property disputes</li>\r\n<li>Building disputes</li>\r\n<li>Probate and inheritance claims</li>\r\n<li>Professional negligence disputes</li>\r\n<li>Boundary/Right of Way disputes&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Debt recovery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Rob has experience of utilising alternative dispute resolution procedures, such as arbitration and mediation and he recognises the importance of adopting a commercial approach, frequently concluding disputes via effective negotiation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul>\r\n<li>Mediation involving high value dispute concerning commercial vehicle hire agreement&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Dilapidations claims for both Claimants and Defendants&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Application for emergency injunction to restrain interference with industrial equipment</li>\r\n<li>Relief From Forfeiture Proceedings for both Applicant and Respondent</li>\r\n<li>Mediation involving high value dispute between builder and customer</li>\r\n<li>Multi-track action involving contractual dispute between education institution and sub-contracted education provider</li>\r\n<li>Chancery actions involving claims under Inheritance (Provision for Family and Dependants) Act 1975</li>\r\n<li>Disputes with Trustees in Bankruptcy regarding equitable shares in matrimonial homes</li>\r\n<li>Fast-track claim involving dispute between air extraction system manufacturer regarding alleged defective installation</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(32, 'Robert Banner', 'Solicitor, Executive Director', 'RobertBanner@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560554 ', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 12:02:16', '2015-03-09 16:44:58', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 9, 'RobertBanner.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 101852, '2011-02-07 12:02:15', 'Robert Banner Personal Injury Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'LLB, Kings College, London', '1976', 'Robert qualified in 1976 and has been a partner in the firm since 1981. After initially spending 12 years specialising in Criminal Law and then Employment Law, for the last 25 years Robert has focused on Personal Injury.  During that time he has developed considerable expertise in all types of cases on behalf of claimants and has dealt with several multi-million pound claims.\r\n\r\nRobert was one of the first solicitors in the area to recognise the importance of management and business planning as far as law firms were concerned.  He took on the role of Managing Partner in the 1980''s and now serves on the Management Executive Committee within Banner Jones Ltd. \r\n\r\nRobert has recently been recognised by the UK Legal 500 and has received the ''Recommended Lawyer'' status for his experience in Personal Injury work.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Robert was elected to the National Executive Committee of the Law Management Section of the Law Society in 2010, and since then he has met with many law firm managers and has written several articles for the section''s magazine ''Managing for Success''.  In January 2014 he took over as Chairman of the section. ', 'Sadly Articled Clerk with a predecessor firm at Marsden Chambers.', 'Annoying the firm''s marketing department by always being the last to complete any request for information... and gardening.', 'Anything alcoholic', 'A weekend in any European city watching Sheffield United win the final of the Champions League  ', 'Answering these questions!', '360_UK_recommended_lawyer_2014.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 7240, '2014-10-01 14:56:56', 'robert banner legal 500', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(33, 'Richard Joy', 'Solicitor, Director', 'RichardJoy@bannerjones.co.uk', '0114 2703790', 'Sheffield', '2011-02-07 12:04:19', '2015-03-09 16:15:10', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 14, 'RichardJoy.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 106834, '2011-02-07 12:04:18', 'Richard Joy Conveyancing Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'BA (Hons) University of Nottingham', '1997', 'Richard Joy worked at Glossops Solicitors in Chesterfield from 1995 - 2004 where he qualified as a Solicitor in 1997. Richard became a partner at Glossops in 2002 who then merged with Banner Jones in 2007. Richard now specialises in Residential Conveyancing.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 'He is also a Trustee of the Chesterfield''s Children Charity C3', 'Prudential - shredding documents', 'Cricket', 'Pint of cold Lager', 'Ashes in Australia', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '167_CQS Logo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 73870, '2012-03-22 12:24:12', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(34, 'Kerry Anderson', 'Costs Lawyer', 'KerryAnderson@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 283021', 'Marsden Street', '2011-02-07 12:05:12', '2014-10-15 13:17:40', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 37, 'Kerry Anderson.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 172303, '2014-10-15 10:04:26', 'Kerry Anderson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '2006', 'Kerry joined Banner Jones in 1996 and is our Head of the Costing department with over 15 years experience in Litigation and Publicly Funded costs.  ', '', '', 'Accounts Clerk at Blake group Vauxhall', 'Socialising with friends and keeping fit', 'A glass of dry white wine', '6 months travelling the world', '5 trips abroad!', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Kerry specialises in drafting Personal Injury and Civil Litigation detailed bills, replies to points of dispute and negotiation.&nbsp;This includes&nbsp;brain injury cases valued up to &pound;3.2mn.</p>\r\n<p>She also&nbsp;prepares publicly funded claims for costs in Family, Care, Crime and Housing cases.&nbsp; In addition Kerry has experience representing paying parties to include preparation of Points of Dispute and negotiation and preparation of Court of Protection bills of costs.</p>\r\n<p>For more information please visit our <a href="../../../page/legal-costing">costing page</a></p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(36, 'Chris Sellars ', 'Solicitor, Executive Director,  Head of BLS', 'ChrisSellars@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 515 / 07787 141807', 'Glumangate / Sheffield', '2011-02-07 12:09:04', '2015-02-19 10:18:10', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 4, 'Chris Sellars.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 167035, '2014-10-15 10:29:58', 'Chris Sellars commercial law', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', ' Durham University', '1992', 'Chris Sellars, BA (Hons)(Dunelm), qualified in 1992 and has a wide ranging role heading up the Business Legal Services team and also the Residential Property team. \r\n\r\n', '', 'Chris is a Fellow of ICBA (Institution of Commercial and Business Agents), a specialist business qualification. \r\n\r\nChris is also a Council Member of the Sheffield Chamber of Commerce.', 'Loading boxes of glasses onto the back of lorries at Dema Glass. It teaches you ambition!', 'Skiing, wakeboarding and playing out with friends', 'Red Wine ', 'Skiing in the Alps and then cruising into Venice before flying to Vegas ', 'Marrying the very lovely Miss Clarke', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Chris has a strong commercial understanding, he is a good negotiator, and very approachable.</p>\r\n<p>Chris specialises in company and commercial work. He advises a wide variety of clients ranging from those with small businesses to major companies. His work includes business sales and purchases, <a href="../../../page/commercial-agreements" target="_blank">commercial agreements</a>, and advice on directors&rsquo; duties. He also advises on&nbsp;<a href="../../../page/insolvency-family" target="_blank">Insolvency </a>and partnership law including limited liability partnerships.</p>\r\n<script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[\r\n  window.___gcfg = {lang: ''en-GB''};\r\n\r\n  (function() {\r\n    var po = document.createElement(''script''); po.type = ''text/javascript''; po.async = true;\r\n    po.src = ''https://apis.google.com/js/platform.js'';\r\n    var s = document.getElementsByTagName(''script'')[0]; s.parentNode.insertBefore(po, s);\r\n  })();\r\n// ]]></script>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '100027917404165376243', 'BannerJChrisS', 'Chris Sellars, BA (Hons)(Dunelm), qualified in 1992 and has a wide ranging role heading up the Business Legal Services team and also the Residential Property team. Chris specialises in company and commercial work. He advises a wide variety of clients ranging from those with small businesses to major companies.'),
(37, 'Simon Wright', 'Solicitor, Executive Director, Head of PI', 'SimonWright@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560551', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 12:11:55', '2015-03-09 15:37:38', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 8, 'SimonWright.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 96996, '2011-02-10 14:45:02', 'Simon Wright Personal Injury Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '1989', 'Simon qualified in 1989 and since that time has specialised in Personal Injury Law and Clinical Negligence claims.  He acts mainly for Claimants, although on occasion he will represent a Defendant.   Simon heads up the department which covers all types of claims including road traffic accidents, workplace accidents, industrial disease, clinical negligence, or in occupier''s liability situations.\r\n \r\nSimon has recently been recognised by the UK Legal 500 and has received ''Recommended Lawyer'' status for his excellence in Personal Injury work.', '', 'He is a member of the Law Society Personal Injury panel and is also a Fellow of the Royal Society of Medicine.', '', '', '', '', '', '135_personal Injury.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 48189, '2011-11-09 16:35:33', '', '', '360_UK_recommended_lawyer_2014.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 7240, '2014-10-01 14:53:16', 'simow wright legal 500', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p><span>He has represented<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="../../../page/claims" target="_blank"><strong>claimants<span>&nbsp;</span></strong></a>seeking damages following a number of nationally reported incidents including the Hatfield Rail Crash and the Manchester Air Disaster. In addition he has represented Claimants in high profile cases of public importance such as Darby v The National Trust<span>&nbsp;</span><span class="st">[2001] EWCA Civ 189&nbsp;</span>which is a leading case in the field of Occupiers Liability.<br /> &nbsp;<br /> Simon has a wealth of experience in cases of upmost severity with his professional involvement in some cases continuing beyond settlement of&nbsp;the claim.&nbsp; In a&nbsp;number of cases Simon&nbsp;has continued to represent his clients by being appointed as a Professional Deputy of the Court of Protection or as Professional Trustee for&nbsp;the injured party where persons have been unable to manage their own affairs following their injuries.&nbsp; &nbsp;Simon feels that&nbsp;his ability to continue to assist people even after the settlement of their claim is a particularly satisfying part of his role.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(39, 'Stephen Gordon', 'Solicitor, Notary Public, Executive Director', 'StephenGordon@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560503', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 12:13:19', '2015-08-17 10:39:10', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 12, 'Stephen Gordon Formal DSC_0019.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 154672, '2015-08-13 15:52:08', 'Stephen Gordon Commercial Solicitor and Notary', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'LLB (University of Sheffield)', '1987', 'Stephen specialises in Commercial Property acting for various landlords and property developers throughout the region.', '', 'As well as a practising Notary, Stephen is the current Treasurer for The Notaries Society. Stephen is also one of the Trustees for the Chesterfield Children''s Charity- C3 and as such regularly gets involved in fundraising events.\r\n\r\nStephen is also a fully trained corporate member of the International Centre for Families in Business, allowing him to specialise in giving family owned businesses legal advice.', 'Halfords Shop Assistant', 'Golf, football, ski, travel & history', 'Wine from Italy', 'Wine tasting on an Italian beach', 'Reaching 50!', '31_ICFIB_LOGO_STRAPnew.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 94666, '2011-11-10 10:39:46', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Stephen deals with the&nbsp;preparation and consideration of Commercial leases as well as <a href="../../../page/commercial-property" target="_blank">Commercial Property </a>freehold sales and purchases. He specialises in healthcare property transactions and has acted for a number of local GP Practices and local Primary Care Trusts.&nbsp;&nbsp; He also has expertise in dealing with Restaurants, Public House&nbsp;and&nbsp;Clubs.&nbsp; Stephen also completes work for&nbsp;charities.</p>\r\n<p>Stephen is also a&nbsp;long established Notary Public dealing with international&nbsp; matters for both private and commercial clients.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Services for your business', '', '', ''),
(41, 'Natalia Shaw', ' Solicitor', 'NataliaShaw@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 560', 'Glumangate', '2011-02-07 12:16:20', '2015-03-09 16:52:57', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 17, 'NataliaShaw.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 99391, '2011-02-10 15:19:28', 'Natalia Shaw Commercial Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'MA Law University of Sheffield ', 'September 2011', 'Natalia studied for her BA Hons Business & Economics degree at Liverpool University before graduating with her MA LAW from the University of Sheffield. She then completed her LPC at Nottingham Law School in June 2008. Natalia joined Banner Jones in May 2009 working in the Dispute Resolution department, primarily focusing on Debt Recovery. Natalia also undertakes Litigation work for one of the Firm''s major clients on uninsured losses arising from vehicle damage.\r\n\r\nNatalia has experience in Commercial Property dealing with the preparation and consideration of commercial leases acting for both Landlord and Tenant. Natalia also assists with commercial freehold sales and purchases.\r\n\r\nNatalia finished her training seat in September 2011 in the Personal Injury department and following a short period assisting in the Residential Property department, Natalia has now returned to Commercial Property.', '', 'Natalia sits on the North East Derbyshire Area Board for Young Enterprise - a charitable organisation that creates a forum in which students may create and launch a product/ service to the open market, allowing them to gain practical business experiences.  \r\n \r\nShe is majorly involved with the fundraising of the organisation, and organises the annual charity ball as well as assisting in the running and development of the program during regular board meetings', 'Telephone sales, selling ''farmers weekly'' magazine during foot and mouth disease', 'Skiing netball tennis running ', 'Ribena ice cold at medium strength', 'Would love to go on safari', 'Skiing ''le face'' unharmed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(42, 'Toby Netting', 'Solicitor, Director, Head of Family', 'TobyNetting@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 209773', 'Marsden Street', '2011-02-07 12:17:15', '2015-03-16 12:32:00', 1, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 6, 'TobyNetting.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 96728, '2011-02-10 15:19:40', 'Toby Netting Family Law Solicitor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'LLB (Hons) University of Sheffield', '1997', 'Toby has specialised in family and matrimonial work since 1996, qualifying in 1997. He joined Banner Jones as a family partner in 2008 to build on the department’s strong reputation and private client work.   Recently Toby has been recognised by the Legal 500 for his ''exceptional'' family work and is now a Recommended Lawyer.\r\n\r\n', '', 'An accredited specialist with Resolution (formerly Solicitors Family Law Association), Toby is also able to help with issues surrounding Children, pre-nuptial and cohabitation agreements and domestic violence.\r\n\r\nToby is the South Yorkshire collaborative group liaison officer. He is actively involved locally, regionally and nationally trying to move non-confrontational collaborative law forward and make it more widely available for suitable cases.\r\n\r\nToby is also a professional member of the International Centre for Families in Business which allows him to give Family Owned businesses specialist legal advice.\r\n\r\nToby has also recently been awarded the Help & Support for Separated Families accreditation.', 'I worked in a commercial house plant nursery in North Wales.', 'Rugby Union (watching not playing these days), reading, gym.', 'Guinness.', 'Snorkelling and diving in the Maldives.', 'Getting through the Great Yorkshire Run with two dodgy knees and too little training.', 'HSSF_colour_mark RGB.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 124572, '2014-06-20 13:28:28', 'HSSF', '', '3_CollaborativeLaw.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 19022, '2011-11-09 16:17:24', 'Collaborative Law', '', 'UK_recommended_lawyer_2014.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 7250, '2014-10-01 14:50:38', '', '', 'A trained <a href="../../../page/mediation" target="_blank">Mediator</a> and experienced Collaborative lawyer, Toby has a lot of experience with high value divorces and always looks to bring a constructive, professional and conciliatory approach to <a href="../../../page/divorce-and-separation" target="_blank">divorce</a>&nbsp;and financial work. He also looks to bring this approach to his work with family business clients, especially in the area of family business disputes.<br />', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(45, 'Helena Downing', 'Solicitor, Director, Head of Care', 'HelenaDowning@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 283014 ', 'Marsden Street', '2011-02-10 15:06:25', '2015-03-13 16:33:07', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 'DSC_9071 Helana Downing.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 135474, '2015-03-13 16:33:06', 'HelenaDowningHeadofCare', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'BA (Hons.) Durham University', '1984', 'In 1994, she joined Banner Jones Middleton as a specialist in family law. Helena is one of the best Family Lawyers in the region and because of this much of Helena''s work involves high value divorce and complex separation cases.\r\n\r\nHelena has been recognised as a ''Recommended Lawyer'' in the 2013 Legal 500 for all of her achievements and excellent work in Family Law.', '', 'Helena is a Resolution Accredited specialist, a member of the Association of Lawyers for Children, and of the Law Society’s Children Panel. In the past she was the Chair of the Derby and Derbyshire Guardian ad Litem and Reporting Officer Committee. \r\n\r\nHelena is also a trained Collaborative Lawyer.\r\n\r\nHelena has been recognised as a ''Recommended Lawyer'' in the 2013 Legal 500 for all of her achievements and excellent work in Family Law.  \r\nHelena has also recently been awarded the Help & Support for Separated Families accreditation.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '323_HSSF_colour_mark RGB.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 126227, '2014-07-17 09:20:47', '', '', '1_ResolutionSpecialist.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 17435, '2011-11-10 10:04:32', '', '', 'UK_recommended_lawyer_2013legal 500.jpg', 'image/pjpeg', 632953, '2013-09-27 10:41:42', '', '', '<p>Helena also deals with <a href="../../../page/financial-settlements" target="_blank">financial issues </a>and matters concerning children of the relationship. She also advises unmarried clients whose relationships have broken up following cohabitation.</p>\r\n<p>An area in which Helena has expertise is <a href="../../../page/care-proceedings" target="_blank">care proceedings</a>, concerning the welfare of children, brought by social services. She generally represents children in these proceedings, but occasionally represents parents.</p>\r\n<p>In her family work, Helena&rsquo;s approach is to try to reduce conflict as much as possible, without compromising her client&rsquo;s position or entitlements.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Services for you and your family', '117466430932572020620', 'BannerJHelenaD', 'In 1994, she joined Banner Jones Middleton as a specialist in family law. Helena is one of the best Family Lawyers in the region and because of this, much of Helena''s work involves high value divorce and complex separation cases. Helena has been recognised as a ''Recommended Lawyer'' in the 2013 Legal 500.'),
(48, 'Isabelle da Silva', 'Paralegal', 'IsabelledaSilva@bannerjones.co.uk', '01246 560 560', 'Sheffield', '2011-03-22 16:50:47', '2015-06-22 15:38:01', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 51, 'Isabella.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 128867, '2013-04-17 11:44:52', 'Isabelle da Silva Business legal services', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'London College of Law', '', 'Isabelle studied for her Business degree in Hong Kong before returning to London where she studied for her GDL and LPC at the College of Law. She joined Banner Jones on completion of her studies in 2010. \r\nShe now utilises both her business background and legal training to advise clients in the Commercial Property and Business Legal Services department.', '', '', 'Waitressing in a cafe', 'Learning Portuguese, baking treats, and playing with my children.', 'Chai Tea Latte', 'Another trip to South America to visit my (husband’s) family.', 'Having my second child: a boy this time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', ''),
(49, 'Carey New', 'Chartered Legal Executive', 'CareyNew@bannerjones.co.uk', '0114 275 5266', 'Sheffield', '2011-06-17 13:35:49', '2015-03-09 16:23:55', 2, 2, 0, NULL, 1, 41, 'carey N prof.JPG', 'image/pjpeg', 122565, '2011-11-21 15:40:42', 'Carey New Conveyancer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Sheffield', '2003', 'Carey studied for her IlLEX qualification at Sheffield College in 1997, taking her final exam in 2001.  She was admitted as a fellow in 2003.  \r\nCarey joins us after 12 years with Norrie Waite & Slater where she was working within their Family Law team.  Carey specialises in all private family law matters including divorce and any related financial matters or children issues, cohabitation issues, pre and post-nuptial agreements, separation deeds and injunctions.\r\nIn April 2014 Carey moved into the residential property team in Sheffield.', '', '', 'Saturday job in a dry cleaners\r\n', 'I remember having those pre children!  They would be going to theatre, running and reading ', 'Red Wine', 'Travelling across Australia in a Winnebago\r\n', 'Cycling from Manchester to Blackpool and helping to raise over £7,000 for Alzheimer’s Research.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', 'Services for you and your family', '', '', '');
